    ("2026-07-12", "GETTING AROUND вҖ” RIDE-APP LINK TEXT MUST BE A DOMAIN (new hard-fail, added 2026-07-12). The Getting Around - Extra Section.html В§1b format '[Ride App Operator]' means the visible link text is the operator's domain (uber.com, bolt.eu, lyft.com, etc.), not the app name ('Uber', 'Bolt', 'Lyft'). The prior per-app link-only check (2026-05-24) verified <a href> presence and child-div count but never checked what the <a> text read. This check scans every рҹҡ• extras-sub вҶ’ transit-box вҶ’ <a> in the Getting Around section and hard-fails any <a> whose visible text contains no dot. Fleet impact at introduction: 47 guides affected (amsterdam, arenal, beijing, bergen, berlin, bologna, bordeaux, boston, boulder, buenos-aires, cayman-islands, chongqing, cinque-terre, dubai, florence, geneva, gothenburg, kyoto, lagos, lake-como, lake-tahoe, ljubljana, los-angeles, luxembourg, lyon, madeira, maui, monaco, naples, orlando, oxford, queenstown, rome, salzburg, scottsdale, seoul, sicily, siena, stockholm, taipei, tallinn, toronto, verona, victoria, zhangjiajie + abu-dhabi). Rule authority: Getting Around - Extra Section.html В§1b."),
    ("2026-07-12", "THREE NEW HARD-FAILS FROM SCREENSHOT REVIEW (Dani), re-applied after concurrent-edit collisions on this shared file. (1) TITLE-HOTEL LINK COLOR-DRIFT GUARD вҖ” .title-hotel must not contain an <a>; only .title-address is the Maps link (Hotel Banner.html В§1). guide-style.css has a color rule for \".title-page .title-address a\" but none for \".title-hotel a\", so a linked hotel name falls through to the global canonical link blue instead of matching the address. Caught: Bhutan's \"COMO Uma Paro\" rendered blue (1/220 guides, now fixed). (2) TRIP OVERVIEW DAY-LABEL REPEAT GUARD вҖ” each .overview-day card's \"Day N\" label must appear exactly once; an undocumented .overview-day-num div duplicated it above .overview-day-title's own \"Day N вҖ“ вҖҰ\" prefix. Caught: Aracaju + Olinda (2/219 guides, now fixed). (3) TOURS NEGATIVE-FINDING BOX PADDING CSS PRESENCE вҖ” \"No qualifying tours on [Platform] in [City].\" sits .entry-body directly under .tours-group, which carries no padding of its own (unlike .extras-sub); without an override the box rendered 0px top / 8px bottom padding (confirmed via Playwright computed style, 37/219 guides affected вҖ” a shared-CSS gap, not per-guide content). Fixed by adding \"#tours .tours-group + .entry-body { padding-top: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }\" to guide-style.css; this check hard-fails if that override is ever removed, rather than re-scanning guide HTML (the .tours-group + .entry-body adjacency is legitimate once the CSS override exists)."),
    ("2026-07-11", "EXTRA SECTION UNIQUENESS вҖ” no extra section written twice (new hard-fail). Each extra section (Cappuccino, Tours, Claude Inspiration, Michelin, вҖҰ) ships exactly once; multiple entries belong INSIDE a single section container, not in a second duplicate container. Claude Inspiration is one <div class=\"claude-inspiration\"> with several <p> blocks (Claude Inspiration - Extra Section.html В§1/В§4), never two separate section containers each repeating the вңЁ Claude Inspiration title; every other section is unique by Guide Structure.html section order. New check enumerates every extra-section container (extras-section OR claude-inspiration) in document order, extracts each one's .extras-title text (empty titles вҖ” the CSS-injected 'Also on this site' block вҖ” excluded), and hard-fails on any title appearing more than once. INVISIBLE UNTIL NOW: a duplicated section renders as two identical headers stacked on the page but passed every prior check (section-order, overview-sync, and closing-div checks all tolerate a repeat). Caught: Montevideo shipped two вңЁ Claude Inspiration containers (theme-teal + theme-coral, the 2nd also missing its id='claude-inspiration') instead of one section with two <p> entries. Fleet scan: 1/219 guides affected (Montevideo only). Rule home: Claude Inspiration - Extra Section.html В§4 + Guide Structure.html section order."),
    ("2026-07-11", "CORE RULES vs VALIDATOR 2ND-PASS RE-AUDIT вҖ” 11 enforcement gaps closed (3 confirmed-missing + 8 candidate, source: 2nd-pass audit 11 July 2026 PM). NEW HARD-FAILS: (1) PHONE/EMAIL BAN (Gap 1) вҖ” RE_EMAIL_PATTERN/RE_PHONE_PATTERN scan the title card and the whole visible body for a phone number or email address; tel:/mailto: hrefs were previously exempt from the target=\"_blank\" check, making them invisible everywhere else (Rules for Claude.html В§7). (2) TOURS рҹҸЁ вҶ’ рҹҡҗ MOTION ROW (Gap 2) вҖ” only рҹҸЁ вҶ” рҹҡҗ / рҹҸЁ вҶҗ рҹҡҗ (tour ends at hotel) are exempt from the рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• return motion row; вҶ’ (pickup-only, tour ends elsewhere) previously dropped it too (Tours - Extra Section.html В§6/В§7). (3) HARDCODED .title-updated (Gap 3) вҖ” the JS-injected \"Updated\" stamp must never appear literally in guide HTML body; only the CSS rule's existence was checked before (Hotel Banner.html В§2a). (4) рҹ“Қ ADDRESS OWN-COUNTRY LEAK (Gap 4) вҖ” a stop address may never contain the guide's own .title-country value, closing a hole the generic any-country comma-split check missed (Links.html В§6). (5) TITLE BANNER EXACTLY 4 LINES (Gap 5) вҖ” .title-page may hold no content beyond the canonical city/hotel/address/country divs; the prior children-list check only caught an extra <div class=\"...\">, not a bare text node (Hotel Banner.html В§2). (6) MICHELIN В§3A RATING REQUIRED (Gap 7) вҖ” an in-hotel heading must carry N.Nвӯҗ В· N+ reviews as a class=\"review-link\" anchor; the inverse (В§3b bans it) was already enforced but the affirmative requirement wasn't вҖ” restructured the entry loop so В§3a/В§3b heading-shape checks no longer contradict each other (Michelin Restaurants - Extra Section.html В§3a; will newly fail Cannes/Rio de Janeiro/Sorrento/Valletta until their В§3a headings are backfilled with a real rating). (7) FOOD DELIVERY INVERSE CHECK (Gap 11) вҖ” negative-finding line and real platform entries may never co-exist, mirroring the guard already on Cappuccino/Local Tastes/Pickleball/Downtown (Food Delivery - Extra Section.html В§2/В§3). (8) CLAUDE INSPIRATION RESERVED-EMOJI (Gap 8, T_NEW8) вҖ” extended beyond section-header icons to also forbid the motion glyphs (рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ•/рҹҡӨ) and рҹ“Қ. NEW WARN-TIER (fuzzy / no numeric threshold defined in CORE RULES, so surfaced for review rather than blocking): (9) alt text reading like a full sentence rather than \"just the subject name\" (Gap 9, Photos Rules.html В§8); (10) a Weekly Closures entry that reads as a singular proper venue rather than a category (Gap 10, Weekly Closures - Extra Section.html В§1); (11) a Train Day outbound/return departure outside the morning/evening window (Gap 6, Day Structure.html В§7). No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator + Validator Index.html only; the flagged Michelin guides need a content backfill in a later pass."),
    ("2026-07-10", "MOTION-BANNER DESTINATION MUST INHERIT THE BANNER FONT (BARE TEXT) вҖ” new hard-fail. The name after вҶ’ in a .hotel-first / .arrive-first / plain .next banner is bare text across the whole compliant fleet (Lisbon/Porto: 'рҹҸЁ From Hotel: рҹҡ• 15 min вҶ’ Cathedral'). Static text carries no styling of its own, so it inherits the SAME font family/size/style/colour as the rest of its banner вҖ” matching the 'рҹҡ¶ N В· рҹҡ• M вҶ’' it follows. That differs by banner type (a .next row is Roboto 14px ITALIC #555 muted grey; a .hotel-first row is upright #1a1a1a) and the check does not need to know it. ANY markup on the destination breaks the inheritance вҖ” an <a href=вҖҰgoogle.com/mapsвҖҰ> recolours it to a{color:#2867c4} blue, a <span>/<font>/inline-style element changes font or colour directly. So the check is structural: the destination segment (everything after the final вҶ’) must contain NO OPENING tag (<[a-zA-Z]) вҖ” a trailing closing tag like </p> from a benign whole-row <p> wrapper (Bora-Bora) does not recolour and is ignored. Dani caught the blue on Aracaju (From Hotel вҶ’ Cathedral) then the muted-greyвҶ’blue drift on a .next row (вҶ’ PalГЎcio). INVISIBLE UNTIL NOW: every motion/opener check strips tags before validating, so the markup slipped through all of them. Scoped to .hotel-first / .arrive-first / EXACT class=\"next\" вҖ” .next-tram / .next-metro excluded (they legitimately carry bracketed board/route/alight anchors per Getting Around.html). Rule home: Motion Rule В§3 + Links.html. Caught + fixed the same day: 4 Brazilian guides from one crib batch had wrapped every banner destination in a Maps link вҖ” Aracaju (21), Olinda (12), JoГЈo-Pessoa (11), Porto-Alegre (9) вҖ” all unwrapped to bare text and re-validated to 0 failures."),
    ("2026-07-11", "STRUCTURE вҖ” EXTRAS-SUB MUST BE FOLLOWED BY CORRECT BODY CONTAINER (new hard-fail). Every .extras-sub heading in every extras section must be immediately followed by the section's designated body container div вҖ” .entry-body for tours/cappuccino/restaurants/downtown/local-tastes/michelin/pickleball; .shows-box for shows; .transit-box for getting-around/day-trips/day-trips-by-train/food-delivery/heads-up; .station-box for stations-near-hotel. When .stop-row divs are used directly after .extras-sub instead, the beige card background (set by the shared token on both .extras-sub + body-box together) only covers the heading line вҖ” all body rows render unstyled with no background. The Aracaju guide (entire cappuccino, restaurants, and downtown sections вҖ” 13 entries) exposed this: the guide looked broken in the browser but passed every validator check because no check verified the sibling container class. New check: for each section, walks every .extras-sub via _walk_balanced_div, finds the next sibling div opening, and hard-fails if its class is not the expected body container. Weekly-closures and skip-list excluded (no .extras-sub entries). Rule home: guide-style.css В§ STYLE A canonical block spec (locked 2026-05-19). Caught by: Aracaju guide visual review."),
    ("2026-07-11", "DAY TRIPS вҖ” 3 VALIDATOR GAPS CLOSED (fleet audit 2026-07-11). (1) EMPTY SECTION NOW HARD-FAILS вҖ” a Day Trips section present with NO body content (no extras-sub entries, no extras-empty negative line) previously downgraded to a warn; now hard-fails. Rule: if the section exists it must have entries or the canonical 'No day trips from {City}.' negative line. Caught: Alaska (empty body), Dubrovnik (dev comment only, no reader-facing line). (2) INVERSE OMIO CHECK вҖ” mainland-China guides (in _OMIO_EXEMPT_CITIES) must NOT include omio.com links; previously the exemption only removed the 'must include Omio' requirement but never banned it. New check hard-fails any рҹҺ« row in a China guide that links to omio.com. Caught: Beijing, Shanghai, Chongqing (all listing Omio). (3) EUROPEAN MIN-5 SET COMPLETED вҖ” _EUROPEAN_GUIDE_CITIES was missing whole countries and several cities: added Hamburg (Germany), Lecce (Italy), MГЎlaga/malaga (Spain), zГјrich (Switzerland вҖ” diacritic alias for existing zurich), Oxford (United Kingdom), Oslo (Norway), KrakГіw/krakow (Poland вҖ” whole country missing), Budapest (Hungary вҖ” whole country missing), Istanbul (Turkey вҖ” whole country missing), Tbilisi (Georgia вҖ” whole country missing). Removed Г…lesund and TromsГё from the set (no train station вҖ” correctly exempt from вүҘ5 floor). Added Santorini and Mykonos to _ISLAND_CITIES (Greek islands, no rail). No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator-only; flagged guides (Oxford 2/5, KrakГіw 4/5, Beijing/Shanghai/Chongqing Omio, Alaska/Dubrovnik empty) need content fixes and re-validation."),
    ("2026-07-10", "CORE RULES AUDIT вҖ” 3 NEW CHECKS + 2 PARTIAL GAPS CLOSED. NEW: (1) CAPPUCCINO CHAIN EXCLUSION вҖ” new _CAP_CHAIN_NAMES list (Starbucks, Dunkin', Peet's, Costa, Tim Hortons, etc.) mirrors the Downtown Restaurants _DR_CHAIN_NAMES pattern; hard-fails any cappuccino entry heading matching a global coffee chain. Rule home: Cappuccino - Extra Section.html В§3. (2) PHOTO LICENSE VALIDATION вҖ” commons_photo.py now fetches extmetadata (license) from the Wikimedia API and records it in photo_provenance.json; photo_provenance.py verify_guide_photos() hard-fails any photo whose license is not CC-BY, CC-BY-SA, Public Domain, or CC0. Rule home: Photos Rules.html В§2. (3) TICKET REGION-SPECIFIC PLATFORM вҖ” Ticketmaster/StubHub/TodayTix are US-only; non-US guides using them hard-fail. Detection: cross-references .title-country with ticket-box link domains. Rule home: Tickets.html В§1. PARTIAL GAPS CLOSED: (4) SHOWS RIDE-ONLY JUSTIFICATION вҖ” ride-only entries (рҹҡ• without рҹҡ¶) now warn when missing a <!-- ride-only: walk NN min --> sentinel documenting that the walk exceeds 40 min. Warn-only (sentinel is a new convention, not yet in CORE RULES). (5) HOTEL BANNER SUBDIVISION вҖ” spelled-out US state names (Florida, California, etc.), Canadian provinces, and European regions now detected as subdivisions in .title-country (previously only abbreviations and comma/dot separators were caught). Gap 6 (ticket-box tour types) confirmed already enforced вҖ” wgiag_subject_strings includes ticket-box <a> text since 2026-05-19. No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator + pipeline only."),
    ("2026-07-10", "DAY TRIPS OPERATOR CHECK вҖ” www. SUBDOMAIN PREFIX FALSE-FAIL FIXED. Toronto's GO Transit booking link (https://www.gotransit.com/...) was hard-failing as a 'non-operator' link despite gotransit.com being whitelisted in _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS since 2026-06-07. Root cause: the match only checked url==host, url.endswith('.'+host), ('/'+host) in url, and ('//'+ host) in url вҖ” none of which match 'https://www.gotransit.com/...' because the 'www.' subdomain sits between '//' and the bare domain, so '//gotransit.com' is never a literal substring. Any operator URL fleet-wide that happens to include a www. prefix was silently false-failing the same way. Fixed by also checking the URL with a leading 'www.' stripped from right after '//'. No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator-only; Toronto's existing GO Transit link is correct as-is and now validates clean."),
    ("2026-07-10", "VALIDATOR DEEP AUDIT WAVE 2 вҖ” 40 bugs fixed (fixes 61-100). Categories: (A) DEAD CODE вҖ” removed dead _pill_links variable, duplicate re.compile calls (_day_block_open_re, _RE_WALK_GLOBAL/_RE_WALK_MIN, _uro_cal_row_re/cal_row_re, _FOOD_RATING_TEXT_RE/_food_review_ok, _CG_ANNOT_RE, _mxc_box_re), duplicate import unicodedata, duplicate guide-style.css check. (B) VARIABLE SHADOWING вҖ” renamed _motion_banner_reвҶ’_tram_motion_re, ticket_link_reвҶ’_ticket_link_re2, canonical_reвҶ’_notshown_canonical_re (all shadowed earlier definitions with different patterns). (C) REGEX BUGS вҖ” Getting Around exclusion regex failed when GA is last section (added |</body> to lookahead); obvious_free_terms had trailing spaces and duplicate entries; _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS used short-substring match (cd.cz/sz.si false-positives) вҶ’ proper domain-boundary check; 6 annotation detection regexes had re.IGNORECASE+[A-Z] matching any lowercase text; VS16 bug in hours-row empty check (рҹҸӣпёҸ? tolerance); cappuccino extra-icon regex missing VS16 variants; 3+ consecutive рҹҸӣпёҸ rows boundary missed entry-body break; Train Day card suffix regex made destination optional (contradicting the required-suffix enforcement); hotel-naming banner regex missing arrive-first class. (D) TOCTOU RACE CONDITIONS вҖ” 10+ sites converted from is_file()+read_text() to _safe_read() helper (Final Gate paths, CORE RULES reader, carousel chain, build state, index reader). (E) SYSTEMATIC next-metro GAP вҖ” next-metro (added 2026-07-05) was missing from 12 boundary/banner regexes across the file: stop-block boundaries (8 sites), bus-ban motion check, hotel-naming protocol, taxi-spacing check. Without it, a .next-metro div was consumed into preceding stop blocks. (F) OTHER вҖ” verification log parse error printed instead of warn(); CAR_FREE_CITIES expanded (hydra/zermatt); stale class names in Guides-Index alphabetical check (overview-sectionвҶ’country, overview-titleвҶ’country-label, idx-cityвҶ’dest-name); Day Trips zip length mismatch warning; added missing national rail operators to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS; eliminated duplicate re.search for booking banned patterns; added arrive-first to taxi-spacing check. No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator-only."),
    ("2026-07-10", "MICHELIN 'NOT SHOWN' FALSE-FAIL FIXED вҖ” a correct line like 'Not shown: 3 вӯҗ more in Atlanta' was hard-failing on guides that had the format exactly right. Root cause: notshown_re has 3 alternatives; alternative 1 ('not\\s+shown') matches 'Not shown' first, then finditer keeps scanning and alternative 3 ('\\d+\\s+вӯҗ.*?more\\s+in\\b') independently re-matches the '3 вӯҗ more in' tail of the SAME line as a spurious second match. That second match's context window (only 10 chars back from the digit) is exactly one character short of reaching the line's leading 'N', so the error message read 'ot shown: 3 вӯҗ...' and always failed the canonical-format check вҖ” even on fully correct lines. Found on Atlanta and Toronto (both had 'ot shown:' in their validator output despite correct guide HTML вҖ” confirmed via direct grep of the raw HTML, which reads 'Not shown: 3 вӯҗ more in Atlanta' with no truncation). Fixed: track each match's context window end and skip any later match whose start falls inside it вҖ” the tail of a line already validated, not a new occurrence. No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator-only; any guide with a correct Not-shown line now validates clean without content changes."),
    ("2026-07-10", "TWO VALIDATOR BUGS FIXED вҖ” both surfaced fixing Cannes's 2 remaining failures, both turned out to be fleet-wide false-fails, not guide-content bugs. (1) FERRY-ONLY LEGS WRONGLY REQUIRED рҹҡ• вҖ” the 'every transit line shows рҹҡ• Uber time' hard-fail (2026-04-30) never accounted for a standalone or line-opening рҹҡў ferry leg, even though Motion Rule.html В§ 1 explicitly documents 'рҹҡў [N min] вҶ’ [Destination]' as complete on its own (same principle as the рҹҡӨ car-free-city rule вҖ” where no road exists, the water crossing IS the ride leg). Cannes's two LГ©rins-Islands ferry legs (no road access, genuinely no Uber possible) were failing; found ~15 other fleet guides shipping the identical bare-рҹҡў pattern already (Seychelles, Sardinia, Toronto, Capri, Turks and Caicos, etc.), confirming this was never a Cannes-specific issue. Added has_ferry exemption: a transit line whose head segment (before the first вҶ’) contains рҹҡў no longer requires рҹҡ•. (2) READ ABOUT LINK CHECK COULD NEVER PASS вҖ” Read-About-Pages.html В§ 2 mandates the READ ABOUT {CITY} link be INJECTED VIA JAVASCRIPT (documented example: document.createElement('a'); a.href='{slug}-read-about.html'; a.textContent='READ ABOUT {CITY}'), but the check added same-day (this file's own 2026-07-10 READ ABOUT entry) only regex-matched a literal static <a href> tag in raw HTML вҖ” which can never see JS-injected content. Verified this was failing on EVERY guide with the JS pattern, including Lisbon, the guide the check's own error message cites as the reference model ('Model: Travel-Website/Guides/Lisbon/lisbon-read-about.html'). Added JS-pattern detection (separate .href and .textContent regex matches) alongside the existing static-tag check вҖ” either satisfies it now. No guide HTML edited for either fix вҖ” validator-only; guides with the correct, spec-compliant content (Cannes, Lisbon, and the fleet generally) now validate clean without any content change."),
    ("2026-07-10", "VALIDATOR DEEP AUDIT вҖ” 19 bugs fixed across the full 26k-line file. HIGH IMPACT (checks silently skipping): (1) Overview card iconвҶ”stop-modifier sync regex used 'В·' separator only вҖ” never matched non-Train day cards using 'вҖ“' (2026-06-16 format); fixed to accept [В·вҖ“]. (2) Same check still required retired рҹҺ’ icon for .self stops; replaced with pass-through. (3) EXTRAS_ORDER Train Stations regex 'Stations Near the Hotel' never matched canonical 'Train Stations Near Hotel'; fixed. (4) EXTRAS_ORDER RNH/Downtown had dead 'Near the Hotel'/'bare Downtown' alternatives; cleaned to match current canonical titles. (5) _QUOTE_CHARS had straight double-quote 3x, missing curly U+201C/U+201D; fixed. (6) 'Missing Uber' check gated on walk presence вҖ” tram-only lines without рҹҡ• slipped through; removed gate. (7) Michelin 'Not shown' class check required zero whitespace after >; added \\s*. (8) box_re used exact class='tour-box' match вҖ” extra classes on div silently skipped the рҹ“Қ-last-row check; fixed to fuzzy \\b match. (9) train_block_re used non-greedy .*?</div> вҖ” wrong nesting depth; replaced with _walk_balanced_div. (10) Ticket-box lead-row regex was greedy, captured entire box body instead of first row; fixed to non-greedy. (11) Day Trips Omio check did unbounded search past next extras-sub вҖ” could check wrong city's box; bounded to entry region. (12) Duplicate-scope detector only recognized H:MM times вҖ” Npm/am formats missed; added alternation. (13) Guides-Index banner check \\bheader\\b false-matched 'section-header' etc.; tightened to exact class. MEDIUM IMPACT: (14) TB-6 used html.find('<script') instead of _tb_script_m.start() вҖ” could find wrong script tag; fixed. (15) NhMM clock-notation check used 200-char comment window (false skip/fire); replaced with full RE_HTML_COMMENT.sub on html. (16) Dead variable _pre removed. (17) _pb_walk_times renamed to _pb_drive_times (held drive times, not walk). (18) RNH duplicate-name tracker appended empty keys; guarded. (19) Comment/code mismatch in filename slug (said underscores, code uses hyphens); fixed comment. No guide HTML edited вҖ” validator-only."),
    ("2026-07-10", "TOURS вҖ” banned nonstandard `.tours-group-label` wrapper class (closes the one real remaining gap from the 2026-07-08 Tours audit's Cluster E 'format misses'). Re-investigation found the other 2 audit-listed format-miss instances were false alarms against the CURRENT validator: Atlanta's missing рҹ•җ and Maldives' missing рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• hotel row are both already hard-failed by the pre-existing entry-format check (рҹ•җ/вҸі/рҹ‘Ҙ presence + unconditional рҹҡ• requirement, both dating to the original 2026-05-20 Tours checks, well before the audit) вҖ” live-tested against atlanta_v1.html and maldives_v1.html today, 0 failures on both, confirming the underlying content was already fixed by other work on this shared workspace before this session touched it. The one genuine, never-checked gap was Bora-Bora's nested `tours-group-label` wrapper (an unstyled class, absent from guide-style.css, that let default heading styles bleed onto entries) вҖ” also already fixed in the guide itself (now plain flat `.tours-group` divs), but nothing banned the class from reappearing. New check hard-fails any `tours-group-label` class inside #tours. No guide HTML edited in this pass вҖ” validator-only."),
    ("2026-07-08", "TOURS AUDIT вҖ” 4 enforcement gaps closed (fleet-wide manual audit of every Tours В§1-В§8 rule against all 207 shipped guides found 28 guides with real deviations that were passing validation). (1) MISSING PLATFORM HEADING (В§5) вҖ” the existing 'platform group never empty' check only inspects .tours-group headings that already exist in the markup; a crib dropping a whole platform sometimes omits its heading ENTIRELY (no heading, no negative line) instead of shipping it empty вҖ” invisible to that check. New check 'all three platform headings present' asserts Viator/GetYourGuide/TripAdvisor headings all exist whenever the section isn't the whole-section-negative case. Fleet: 19 guides / 25 platform slots (Aruba, Big-Island, Cayman-Islands, Chongqing, Curacao, Kauai, La-Jolla, Milan, Oahu, Pensacola, Portland, Sedona, Sint-Maarten, Taipei, Yellowstone, + Fortaleza/Glacier-National-Park with all 3 missing). (2) MANGLED REVIEW COUNT (В§6) вҖ” a thousands-separator comma corrupted into a stray middle-dot (e.g. '4.7вӯҗ В· 1 В·176+ reviews' instead of '4.7вӯҗ В· 1,176+ reviews') was invisible because the existing reviews-count regex greedily matches only the LAST digit group before 'reviews', so '176' alone cleared the вүҘ6 bar and passed silently. New _TOURS_MANGLED_REVIEWS_RE detects the two-digit-groups-split-by-В· shape directly. Fleet: Annecy, Cannes, Turin, Pasadena (7 entries). (3) BARE CYCLING/BIKING (В§2 excluded types) вҖ” banned_tour_types only listed 2-word phrases ('cycling tour(s)', 'bicycle tour(s)'); titles with the word alone in a different position ('Ubud: Downhill Cycling with Volcano and Rice Terraces', 'Napa Valley Cycling Wine Tour') didn't match any phrase and shipped. Added bare 'cycling' + 'biking' tokens (word-boundary gated, same list already scanned against Tours .extras-sub <strong> titles). Fleet: Bali, Napa. (4) NON-CANONICAL NEGATIVE-FINDING WORDING (В§8) вҖ” the canonical-wording regex used a greedy '.+' for the [City] placeholder, so embellished text ('No qualifying tours in Columbia on Viator, GetYourGuide, or TripAdvisor meeting the 4.5вҳ… В· 6+ review bar.') still matched the 'in .+\\.' shape and passed. Added a second pass that rejects platform names / review / rating / star / meeting / platform language leaking into the captured city text. Also discovered and fixed a second, larger hole in the same check: it only ever scanned .entry-body divs, so the WHOLE-SECTION-negative case (wrapped in .extras-empty, per Guide Structure) was never wording-checked at all вҖ” Fortaleza ('No tours found qualifying at 4.5вҳ… and 6+ reviews for Fortaleza at time of build.') and Glacier-National-Park ('No tour operators meet the minimum ratings threshold for Glacier National Park tours.') were shipping completely free-form sentences, invisible until this pass. Fleet: Columbia, MaceiГі, Fortaleza, Glacier-National-Park. No guide HTML edited in this pass вҖ” validator-only; the 28 flagged guides still need per-guide fixes + re-validation."),
    ("2026-07-06", "PICKLEBALL T5 вҖ” FIX SILENT PASS BUG (detected via verify). T5 was detecting US eligibility from .title-address state code (Patterns A/B/C), but hotel addresses use 'Street В· Neighborhood' format (Hotel Banner.html) which never includes a state code вҖ” so trip_state was None for nearly all US guides and the gate silently skipped. Fixed: primary signal switched to .title-country == 'United States' (always present, required by Hotel Banner.html В§1). State-code parser kept for informational hint in check messages only. Fleet impact: all 189 US guides missing pickleball now hard-fail T5 as intended. Non-US guides unchanged вҖ” title-country is never 'United States' for them."),
    ("2026-07-06", "PICKLEBALL EXPANDED TO ALL US STATES (Dani-approved). Previously CA/AZ/OR only. Now every US guide (all 50 states + DC, detected from .title-address state code) MUST carry a pickleball section or hard-fails. PICKLEBALL_ELIGIBLE_STATES updated from {CA,AZ,OR} to all 51 codes. Guides with no pickleball section will fail T5 until rebuilt. Non-US guides: unchanged вҖ” section silently omitted."),
    ("2026-07-06", "PICKLEBALL RULE CHANGE вҖ” 25 min walk вҶ’ 25 min drive (Dani-approved rule change). Pickleball - Extra Section.html В§2/В§3/В§4 updated. Validator updated to match: (1) рҹҡ• drive time is now REQUIRED (was: рҹҡ¶ required + рҹҡ• optional); (2) рҹҡ¶ walk time is now OPTIONAL (add when also walkable); (3) cap check changed from вүӨ28 min walk to вүӨ28 min drive (рҹҡ•); (4) ordering check uses drive times (рҹҡ•) instead of walk times (рҹҡ¶); (5) row-order anchor changed from рҹҡ¶ to рҹҡ•; (6) negative-finding regex updated: 'within 25 min walk' вҶ’ 'within 25 min drive'. Fleet impact: guides with рҹҡ•-only entries (no рҹҡ¶) now pass; entries with рҹҡ¶ but no рҹҡ• will hard-fail (must add drive time). Pickleball sections in CA/AZ/OR guides should be rebuilt with courts within 25 min drive."),
    ("2026-07-05", "VALIDATOR AUDIT вҖ” 11 enforcement gaps closed (rule-by-rule audit of every format spec). (1) TR-7 BANNED PILLS вҖ” the 'Also on this site' rail now hard-fails City Transit Cards / SIM Cards Abroad / Tipping Guide / Airport Lounges / Climate Finder (TR-4 deliberately tolerated unknown pills; validate_also_on_site_pills.py was never wired into ship; brain_check skips the unstamped shipping guide вҖ” so banned pills shipped, caught only next session). (2) TICKET ORDER вҖ” рҹҺҹ lead row now hard-fails a booking domain/platform placed LEFT of the N.Nвӯҗ rating (Tickets В§2a/2b: Title В· rating В· [reviews В·] platform); keys on domain/platform-left-of-вӯҗ, not segment index, so subtitle dots don't false-fail (only KrakГіw's 9 domain-first rows trip it). (3) TRAM SILENT NO-OP вҖ” the 3 tram checks anchored on the literal heading 'рҹҡҺ Tram', so 'рҹҡҺ T1 Tram' / 'рҹҡҺ No tram foundвҖҰ' dodged them all; broadened anchor to рҹҡҺ[^<]* (any рҹҡҺ-led heading). (4) TRAM/METRO/FERRY MOTION FORMAT вҖ” рҹҡў/рҹҡқ now get the full вүҘ60minвҶ’hours + no-0-min enforcement in _validate_motion_row (were 'has a digit' only); рҹҡҺ excluded (line-number inline form, validated by the sub-line check). (5) METRO SUB-LINE вҖ” Motion Rule В§1 defines a 'рҹҡқ metro' sub-line 'same inline pattern as tram', but the word-'metro' ban false-failed it and there was no home: added .next-metro (banner recognizer + metro-word exemption inside it + shape check mirroring tram + guide-style.css). (6) TRIP OVERVIEW EoI вҖ” .overview-day cards now hard-fail any EoI/foreign content (<img>/<p>/<ul>/<table>/<hN>/media); only two retired divs were banned before, so any new content class passed vacuously (days-only grid). (7) TOURS + RIDE-APP вҖ” added Tours В§3 platform grouping ORDER (all ViatorвҶ’all GetYourGuideвҶ’all TripAdvisor; 0 fleet interleaving) + ride-app negative-finding canonical wording 'No ride apps available in [City].' (tram had it, ride-apps didn't). (8) PICKLEBALL вҖ” every entry now requires a рҹҡ¶ walk time; a рҹҡ•-only entry was accepted and was invisible to the вүӨ28-min cap + closest-first ordering (Pickleball В§2/В§3). (9) HEDGING вҖ” 'approximately N hours/minutes' now caught (regex only matched abbreviated units with a trailing \\b; spelled-out 'hours'/'minutes' evaded, unlike the correctly-built 'roughly'/'around'). (10) WEEKLY CLOSURES вҖ” Oxford day list 'Monday, Wednesday, & Friday' (the spec's own valid example) was rejected: separator now repeats so ', & ' is consumed as two separators. (11) HEADS UP вҖ” heading-format check LABEL said 'REQUIRED leading вқ—пёҸ' while the code correctly BANS it (2026-06-24 rule); label + adjacent 'no emoji' label + _SECTION_ICON_ALLOWLISTS entry + stale comment corrected to match. Fleet impact: TR-7 / ride-app wording / tours order / metro / EoI = 0 current guides (preventive); ticket order = KrakГіw; pickleball рҹҡ¶ = 5 guides (Phoenix/Palm-Desert/San-Jose/Santa-Cruz/Malibu) вҖ” all genuine spec violations that were slipping through. No guide HTML edited in this pass."),
    ("2026-07-05", "GETTING AROUND В§1b вҖ” ONE OPERATOR PER рҹҡ• ENTRY + NAMED HEADING (Dani 2026-07-05: 'why this is not failing?' вҖ” the 'рҹҡ• Ride Apps вҶ’ Uber В· Bolt' aggregate). The existing per-app link-only check (2026-05-24) only counted child <div>s + link presence, so two operators joined by 'В·' inside one div (1 div, contains an <a>) sailed through, as did a generic 'Ride Apps' placeholder heading. Two new checks in the GETTING AROUND block: (A) MULTI-OPERATOR BOX вҖ” each рҹҡ• extras-sub's transit-box must hold exactly one <a>; >1 hard-fails (each ride app is its own extras-sub + box, no 'В·'-joined row). (B) GENERIC HEADING вҖ” the рҹҡ• heading must name the operator (Uber/Bolt/Grab/вҖҰ), not the category label 'Ride App(s)' / 'ride-hailing' / 'rideshare'. Rule authority: Getting Around - Extra Section.html В§1b (singular 'рҹҡ• [Ride App]' + one '[Ride App Operator]'; all 149 conforming guides name the operator). Companion same pass: 57 drifted guides normalized to per-app format; Validator Index.html + Cleanliness Checks.md updated. Format fix only вҖ” data-updated NOT bumped."),
    ("2026-06-28", "STATUS DOTS + DELTA ROUTES FINAL GATE. Two new hard-fail checks added to the FINAL GATE (end of validation): (1) STATUS DOTS вҖ” city must appear on a bullet line in Brain/Reference/Status Dots вҖ” guides_index.md; absence means the guide shipped without ever being added to the status tracking doc and the index dot can't reflect reality. (2) DELTA ROUTES вҖ” city must have a card with data-guide=\"FolderName\" in Trip-Essentials/Delta-Routes-SEA.html; Seattle is exempt (origin city). Both run after the world-map-pin check, before Open Questions. Previously these were only enforced at guide_tools.py ship time; now the static validator also catches them (consistent with the index-listing / map-pin / also-on-this-site pattern)."),
    ("2026-06-28", "GUIDE CARD AND STATUS GATE (FINAL GATE). New hard-fail check: every guide listed in Guides-Index.html MUST have data-status=\"want\" attribute on its dest-card element (the blue dot indicator for 'want to go'). Detects missing or incorrect status before ship. Reason: 93 guides were shipped without the data-status attribute; new guides must default to 'want to go' with proper visual indicator. Runs at the end of validation (FINAL GATE) alongside index-listing and map-pin checks (line ~25400). Provides specific guidance to add attribute to dest-card. Companion fix (same session): all 201 guides in Guides-Index.html now have proper data-status values (195 want + 6 been)."),
    ("2026-06-28", "GUIDE HTML FILENAME PATTERN CHECK (ENHANCED). Hard-fail check: guide HTML files must follow the {city}_v*.html pattern where {city} is derived from the folder name (e.g., Azores/ вҶ’ azores_v1.html, Cairo/ вҶ’ cairo_v2.html). Detects non-compliant names: Cairo.html, Lake Tahoe.html, guide_v1.html, or any non-city-specific filename before they ship. The filename MUST start with the city slug (folder name converted to lowercase, spaces/hyphens вҶ’ underscores). Reason: Azores shipped as guide_v1.html; Cairo and Lake Tahoe as Cairo.html/Lake Tahoe.html; this check enforces city-specific naming so all guides are discoverable and versioned consistently. Runs early in validate() (line ~383) before any content checks. Provides specific guidance on rename (e.g., 'Found: guide_v1.html in Azores/ вҖ” rename to azores_v1.html')."),
    ("2026-06-27", "TITLE-COUNTRY FULL NAME (Dani-approved). New hard-fail check: .title-country must be the country's full name вҖ” no abbreviation, no country code, no subdivision (state/province/territory/region). Detection: a comma or middle-dot in the value = subdivision; a short all-caps token (вүӨ4 letters, dots optional) = abbreviation/code. Empty is left to the pre-existing presence check. Rule home: Hotel Banner.html В§1 Entry. Companion: 9 live guides normalized (US/USA/USВ·Colorado/Florida,USA вҶ’ United States earlier this session; UK вҶ’ United Kingdom, NZ вҶ’ New Zealand, UAE вҶ’ United Arab Emirates in this pass). Validator Index.html + Cleanliness Checks.md updated."),
    ("2026-06-27", "TR-6 added вҖ” required pills check. All 7 canonical 'Also on this site' pills must be present: Weather В· Time Zones В· Plug Adapter В· Currency В· Safety Guide В· Visas В· Stats. European Train Guide exempt (EU only). Previously the validator only checked ORDER of pills that were present вҖ” absence of a pill was not caught. Victoria failure mode: missing Time Zones / Plug Adapter / Currency slipped through."),
    ("2026-06-26", "TRIP RESOURCES checks TR-3, TR-4, TR-5 added. TR-3: extras-title div in #also-on-this-site must be EMPTY вҖ” title 'Also on this site' is injected by CSS ::before; hardcoded text bypasses CSS. TR-4: pill order enforced вҖ” canonical sequence: Weather В· Time Zones В· Plug Adapter В· Currency В· Safety Guide В· Visas В· Stats В· European Train Guide (EU guides only, always last); out-of-order pairs hard-fail. TR-5: anchor correctness вҖ” #Eurozone is never valid (use per-country: #France / #Italy / etc.); multi-word country names must use underscores matching the target-page getElementById IDs (Czech_Republic, United_Kingdom, New_Zealand, Cayman_Islands, Sint_Maarten); dashes silently miss the scroll-to jump."),
    ("2026-06-26", "TITLE CARD FONT SIZE LOCK. New check: no inline font-size override on .title-hotel / .title-address / .title-country вҖ” all three locked at 14px in guide-style.css (Hotel Banner.html В§2a, approved 2026-06-26). An inline style override would silently break the standard. Brain_check enforces the CSS source values; this check blocks per-guide overrides in HTML."),
    ("2026-06-25", "STYLESHEET HREF + MICHELIN-COUNT CLASS. (1) Stylesheet href regex updated: guide_v3.css вҶ’ guide-style.css (CSS file renamed 2026-06-25). (2) New check: Michelin 'Not shown' div must carry class=\"michelin-count\" вҖ” without it the 14px top-margin spacing rule in guide-style.css has no effect and the line runs flush against the last restaurant entry."),
    ("2026-06-24", "TRIP RESOURCES section checks added (TR-1, TR-2). TR-1: the 'Also on this site' extras-title must not carry an inline color or border-bottom style вҖ” the gold colour (var(--c-brand) = #8a6c1a) and matching underline bar come from .extras-title in guide-style.css; an inline style would silently override them. TR-2: every <a> inside the also-on-this-site block must carry class=\"also-on-this-site-pill\" вҖ” that class is what supplies the gold border (#c8a44a) from guide-style.css; a pill with a missing or renamed class gets no border styling. Both checks are no-ops when the also-on-this-site block is absent (it is conditional)."),
    ("2026-07-05", "TITLE-CITY FOLDER SLUG DETECTION (Dani 2026-07-05). New hard-fail: .title-city must use the real city name, not the folder-convention slug. Folder names use hyphens as space replacements (e.g. Carmel-by-the-Sea/); copying the folder name into .title-city produces 'CARMEL-BY-THE-SEA' вҖ” wrong. Detection: strip the ' В· SUFFIX' from title-city, build the expected folder slug (lowercase, spacesвҶ’hyphens), compare against the actual parent folder name. An exact match means the display name was copied verbatim from the folder slug rather than written as a human-readable name вҖ” hard-fail with guidance to replace hyphens with spaces. Carmel by the Sea was the trigger incident (shipped 2026-07-05)."),
    ("2026-06-24", "DAY TRIPS вҖ” SNCF Connect link text must be exactly 'SNCF Connect' (Dani 2026-06-24: Strasbourg/Marseille/Annecy/others had 'sncf-connect', 'sncf-connect.com', or bare 'SNCF'). New check: every <a> in the Day Trips section whose href contains 'sncf-connect' must have anchor text exactly 'SNCF Connect'. CORE RULES edited: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§2 now specifies 'SNCF Connect' as the canonical label. EXPECTED to fail: 9 guides вҖ” Strasbourg (5), Marseille (2), Annecy (1), and others."),
    ("2026-06-21", "SKIP LIST FOOTNOTE CURRENCY CHECK ADDED (Dani 2026-06-21). New hard-fail in the SKIP LIST block: when a city has a `## City` entry in the Cities Skip List (Brain.md Part 4), its guide's 'Skipping:' footnote venue set must EQUAL the current skip-list entries вҖ” no missing venues, no extras (alias-aware, substring-tolerant matching). Closes the gap where adding a venue to the skip list and later rebuilding a guide silently shipped a stale footnote: the prior checks only enforced that the footnote EXISTED, never that it MATCHED. This enforces the new Skip List - Extra Section.html В§ 5 (Recheck on rebuild) вҖ” editing the skip list never triggers a rebuild, but any guide rebuilt with new content must bring its footnote into parity. Companion same pass: Skip List - Extra Section.html В§ 5 added (CORE RULES вҖ” approved, checksums regenerated), В§5 calibration anchor added to the spec self-check, Validator Index.html + CLAUDE.md DriftyCat updated."),
    ("2026-06-21", "LAST-UPDATED STAMP MOVED TO TOP + made explicit; FOOTNOTE FOOTER REMOVED. (1) The 'Updated Month Year' stamp was relocated from the bottom of the guide to the top (right-aligned last row of .title-page, font-size:13px color:#9a948a) and its source changed from document.lastModified to an EXPLICIT data-updated=\"YYYY-MM\" attribute on the toolbar-mount div. Rationale: lastModified bumps on every file touch (bug fix, validation re-stamp, GitHub Pages deploy вҶ’ all guides read the deploy month), the opposite of content-currency. data-updated only moves on a genuine content refresh. All 155 guides seeded data-updated=\"2026-06\". TB-11 REPURPOSED: was the FOOTNOTE_RETIRED guard check; now hard-fails any guide whose toolbar-mount lacks a well-formed data-updated=\"YYYY-MM\". (2) footnote.js (footer sharing link, retired 2026-06-06) fully REMOVED вҖ” archived to Travel/archive/footnote.js.retired-2026-06-21; toolbar.js loader + FOOTNOTE_RETIRED guard + noFootnote read deleted; data-no-footnote stripped from all 181 pages; build_currency.py + build_travel_stats.py templates updated; brain_check.py footnote.js existence/stray checks removed. TB-9 reworded retiredвҶ’removed (mechanics unchanged: loads toolbar.js + no inline footer div + no direct footnote.js). Companion docs same pass: Brain/Reference/Toolbar.html В§6 (Removed) + В§10 (rewritten for data-updated), Change Cascade.html (stamp notes), Validator Index.html (TB-9/TB-11), Navigation.html, Rules for Claude.html В§4 + CLAUDE.md DriftyCat (CORE RULES вҖ” approved, checksums regenerated)."),
    ("2026-06-20", "SIX VALIDATOR FIXES (A-F). A: links_no_blank вҖ” relative-path hrefs (../../, ./, ../) now excluded from the 'missing target=_blank' check; they are internal navigation links and never need _blank. B: eoi_canonical_order now has 16 entries вҖ” 'also-on-this-site' added at the end (after skip-list); eoi_conditional_set updated to include 'also-on-this-site'; check labels updated from 15-element / 15 canonical to 16-element / 16 canonical. C: Overview-extra-link exempt set expanded вҖ” 'also-on-this-site' added alongside 'skip-list' so guides with a also-on-this-site block don't fail the 'every extras-section has a matching overview link' check. D: Claude Inspiration T1 misplacement regex updated вҖ” also-on-this-site (id='also-on-this-site') is now exempt alongside skip-list from the 'no extras-section after CI' check; the negative lookahead was extended to (?:skip-list|also-on-this-site). E: Weather check вҖ” weather_plain is now built from html with the <!-- also-on-this-site -->вҖҰ<!-- /also-on-this-site --> block stripped first, so resource-pill link text (e.g. 'Climate Finder') can't trigger weather heading drift checks. F: Inline text-decoration check вҖ” similarly strips the also-on-this-site block before scanning for inline style='text-decoration:...' on <a> tags, so pill <a> styling inside the resources block can't trigger the ban."),
    ("2026-06-20", "NO-PHOTO-REASON SENTINEL REQUIRED (Dani 2026-06-20). Every .stop-photos-empty wrapper must now be preceded (within 600 chars) by <!-- no-photo-reason: {reason вүҘ 10 chars} --> confirming Commons was fully searched. Previously the single allowed empty stop had no written-reason requirement вҖ” it could ship with no explanation. New check K hard-fails any empty wrapper missing the sentinel. If a second stop genuinely has no Commons photo and the reason comment is already in use for a different stop, the second stop must be replaced with a stop that has available photos rather than left empty. Photos Rules.html В§7 updated; Validator Index.html and Cleanliness Checks.md item 216b updated; checksums regenerated. Format: <!-- no-photo-reason: no suitable licensed photo found on Commons for {stop name} -->"),
    ("2026-06-20", "PHOTO EMPTY CAP TIGHTENED вүӨ2 вҶ’ вүӨ1 (Dani 2026-06-20). Guide-level 'No pictures found.' cap reduced from at most 2 to at most 1. Two or more empty photo wrappers in a single guide now hard-fail regardless of whether each wrapper is individually valid. Rationale: a single genuinely unfindable stop is acceptable; two or more signals the harvest step was skipped or abandoned. Photos Rules.html В§7 updated with the guide-level cap; Validator Index.html entry updated. The check label updated from 'at most 2' to 'at most 1'."),
    ("2026-06-20", "TITLE PAGE PALETTE FOLLOWS 2026-06-20 REDESIGN вҖ” the title card was redesigned today (commits 3bb19927 'Match guide title to site' вҶ’ 6f868a0f) from the 2026-06-15 dark-bg/light-text palette to a light-bg/dark-text palette matching the site header: .title-page background:none, .title-city/.title-hotel/.title-country вҶ’ #3d3a32, .title-address вҶ’ #6a6660 (set in Guide Style.css + guide-style.css). The validator allowlist was never updated, so all 134 live guides hard-failed 'Link-color overrides match allowlist' (offender: .title-page .title-address a #6a6660 vs stale-expected rgba(255,255,255,0.60)). Fixes: (1) LINK_COLOR_ALLOWLIST '.title-page .title-address a' rgba(255,255,255,0.60) вҶ’ #6a6660; (2) the local-<style>-override canonical set {#f5e0b8, rgba(255,255,255,0.60)} вҶ’ {#3d3a32, #6a6660} (+ comment). No guide HTML touched вҖ” the guides inherit guide-style.css and were correct; the validator was stale (same pattern as the 2026-06-11 / 2026-06-01 allowlist-vs-CSS sync fixes)."),
    ("2026-06-19", "AUDIT BACKLOG вҖ” 5 checks from 2026-06-17 Core Rules audit (B1/B2/B3/B4/B5). B1: global body-wide bare-placeholder scan вҖ” TBD/TODO/FIXME/'fill in later'/'tour TBD' in visible body text now hard-fail (title-page already caught these; body was missed). B2: вүӨ4-day Train Day prohibition now enforced вҖ” the short-guide branch silently passed even when Train Day cards were present; now checks _quota_train_day_count == 0 and hard-fails if any Train Days found (Day Structure В§6 'must NOT include'). Threshold uses TOTAL days (including Train Days) вҖ” a 6-day guide with 3 Train Days is not a 3-day guide; only guides with вүӨ4 total days in the overview are short guides. B3: stop-count floor вүҘ4 flipped from warn() to check() (hard fail) вҖ” sentinel exemption (<!-- day-count: N вҖ” reason --> with carve-out keyword) still suppresses; Validator Index already documented this as enforced. B4: _MOTION_LEAD_RE broadened from [рҹҡ¶рҹҡ•рҹҡў] to [рҹҡ¶рҹҡ•рҹҡўрҹҡқрҹҡҺ] вҖ” metro (рҹҡқ) and tram (рҹҡҺ) consecutive-motion-row check now fires correctly. B5: CSS text-transform ban broadened from one exact pattern (a, a:visited { text-transform: lowercase }) to any text-transform value on any <a>-targeting or cascading selector (Trip Overview В§4 'any global text-transform on anchors')."),
    ("2026-06-17", "GETTING AROUND В§2 TRAM вҖ” negative-finding line REMOVED + tram no longer mandatory-present (Dani 2026-06-17: 'tram has to be checked and the negative line has to come out вҖ” cribs are lazy and dont check when we had the other way'). Mirrors the В§4 Ferry fix: a tram is always researched, the рҹҡҺ Tram subsection ships ONLY when a usable tram exists, and a no-tram city OMITS the subsection entirely. CORE RULES edited: Getting Around - Extra Section.html В§2a/В§2b вҖ” dropped 'If no tram is available, ship the negative-finding line: No tram available in [City].'; В§2a now says always-check + omit-when-none (checksums regenerated, doc_workshop_validator clean). Validator: (1) the 'TRAM SECTION MANDATORY' check (subsection OR negative line) is replaced by 'TRAM NEGATIVE LINE IS DRIFT' вҖ” a 'No tram available' / 'does not have a tram' line hard-fails; (2) TRAM TEMPLATE ADHERENCE reduced from 4 templates to the 2 positive ones (the two negative templates retired). Narrowed the drift regex so template 2 ('[City] has a tram system вҖҰ No tram rides on this trip.' вҖ” a positive entry, tram exists) is NOT caught. EXPECTED to fail: every guide currently shipping a tram negative-finding line, until the subsection is removed or replaced with a real tram entry (Dani: guides failing is fine)."),
    ("2026-06-17", "WIKIPEDIA REQUIRED PER STOP вҖ” HARD FAIL (Dani 2026-06-17). Every stop-block must carry a рҹ“– Wikipedia row. The old <!-- no-wikipedia: --> sentinel NO LONGER exempts a stop. Sole allowance: a guide may omit the рҹ“– on AT MOST ONE stop, and only when a full written explanation (>= 40 chars) is logged in the guide log _build/verification_log.json as an entry with platform 'wikipedia-omit' (or result 'OMIT'). Zero omissions = fine; one omission = needs the logged explanation; two or more = hard fail regardless. EXPECTED to fail: every guide currently relying on inline no-wikipedia sentinels (вүҲ70 guides) until each missing stop gains a рҹ“– link or the single allowed omission is logged."),
    ("2026-06-17", "LINKS В§3 вҖ” booking-URL 'within 90 days' staleness check REMOVED (Dani-approved; rule wins). Links.html В§3 states a logged PASS permanently clears the warning with no age expiry, and Wikipedia PASS was already exempt вҖ” but a separate hard check still failed any bot-blocked booking-URL (Viator/GYG/Michelin/TripAdvisor) verification_log.json entry older than 90 days. Removed the _stale/_today/_age logic and the 'within 90 days' check(); the 'has a log entry' and 'is PASS' checks stay, and verified_on is still format-validated (a malformed date still flags). No CORE RULES edit needed вҖ” Links.html already matched the kept behavior. Effect: guides with PASS log entries >90d old no longer fail (e.g. one of Zurich's fails clears)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "вҸ° AVG TIME SPENT now required on EVERY stop + рҹҺ’ retired (Dani 2026-06-16). (1) The вҸ° requirement was gated on the рҹҺ’ self-guided marker; рҹҺ’ is retired from guides, so the gate is removed вҖ” every stop now needs a stop-level вҸ° (Stops Structure В§3a/В§3b). Sole exception: guided рҹ“…-led .tour-box stops carry вҸі instead. EXPECTED to fail: 26 stops across ~7 guides (Kyoto 7+, Big Island, Singapore, Chicago, Bahamas, Boston, Maui). (2) Removed dead рҹҺ’ logic: tour-first рҹҺ’ note check tombstoned, is_self_guided term dropped from the вҸ°-on-guided check. The backpack-emoji ban (рҹҺ’ in guide HTML hard-fails) stays вҖ” catches the one straggler (Strasbourg)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "STOPS В§1c вҖ” generic markets / bookshops / retail arcades banned as STOPS (Dani 2026-06-16, Stops Structure audit). The named blocklist (T1) only caught the 12 famous venues; this T1b check flags ANY .stop-name containing market/bazaar/souk/souq/mercado/mercato/marchГ©/markthalle/bookshop/bookstore/livraria/librairie/libreria/bouquiniste/arcade вҖ” banned 'of any kind, including iconic ones' (В§1c). Scoped to .stop-name (descriptions may mention a nearby market). EXPECTED to fail: Montreal (Bonsecours/Jean-Talon Market), Porto (Mercado do BolhГЈo), Seattle (Pike Place Market), Vancouver (Granville Island Public Market)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TOURS 5/5/5 вҖ” per-platform minimum flipped from WARN to HARD FAIL unless well-documented (Dani 2026-06-16, reversing the 2026-05-24 warn; 'it has been abused too'). Below 5 on Viator/GetYourGuide/TripAdvisor now fails UNLESS the <!-- low-count: reason --> comment (a) names each short platform AND (b) carries a non-generic reason вҖ” generic filler ('small market', 'limited availability', 'few tours', 'thin market') with no per-platform accounting is the abuse pattern and does not exempt. Containment for lazy cribs: the only exit from 5/5/5 is a specific, per-platform, auditable reason. Merged the old per-platform-min warn and the separate low-count-comment-required check into one. CORE RULES: Tours - Extra Section.html В§5 updated to state the documentation bar (checksums regenerated, doc_workshop_validator clean). EXPECTED to fail: ~105 guides below 5/5/5, of which the generically-documented ones (Palm Desert, Dublin, Montreal, etc.) fail; well-documented ones (Lima, etc.) pass."),
    ("2026-06-16", "DAY OPENER вҖ” вҶ’ first stop now enforced. Motion Rule В§3a/В§3b opener is 'рҹҸЁ From Hotel: рҹҡ¶ N В· рҹҡ• M вҶ’ [First stop]', but _validate_motion_row strips the 'вҶ’ dest' before checking, so the destination was never verified. New check: every .hotel-first opener div must end with 'вҶ’ {non-empty destination}'. Closes audit gap #1."),
    ("2026-06-16", "DAY TRIPS вҖ” Omio booking link text must be exactly 'Omio' (Dani 2026-06-16, Berlin: mixed 'Omio'/'omio'/'omio.com'). CORE RULES edited: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§2 template '[omio]' вҶ’ 'Omio', coverage-exception paragraph now states the entry is written exactly as 'Omio' in title case (checksums regenerated, doc_workshop_validator clean). New check: every <a> in the Day Trips section whose href contains 'omio' must have anchor text exactly 'Omio'. Scoped to Omio-covered regions (China-exempt). EXPECTED to fail: many guides incl. Berlin, Zurich (omio.com)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "GETTING AROUND рҹҡў FERRY вҖ” negative-finding line is now DRIFT (Dani 2026-06-16: 'remove that from the rules вҖҰ this was a drift'). CORE RULES edited: Getting Around - Extra Section.html В§4 removed 'If no ferry is relevant, ship No ferry available in [City].'; the Ferry subsection is now omitted entirely when no relevant ferry route exists (checksums regenerated, doc_workshop_validator clean). New check: a рҹҡў Ferry extras-sub followed by a ferry negative-finding line ('No ferry available', 'does not have a ferry', 'no ferry') hard-fails вҖ” omit the whole subsection instead. EXPECTED to fail: guides carrying the old line (e.g. Amalfi)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TOURS вҖ” platform group never empty + motion-vs-pickup (Dani 2026-06-16, Azores). (1) EMPTY PLATFORM GROUP: a .tours-group heading (Viator/GetYourGuide/TripAdvisor) must be followed by вүҘ1 рҹ“… entry OR the fixed negative-finding line 'No qualifying tours on [Platform] in [City].' before the next group/section end вҖ” a bare heading with nothing after it hard-fails (Tours В§5+В§8). Caught: Azores 'TripAdvisor' heading with nothing after it. (2) MOTION-VS-PICKUP (Tours В§6): рҹҸЁ вҶ” рҹҡҗ / рҹҸЁ вҶҗ рҹҡҗ (tour returns to hotel) must ship NO motion banner; рҹҸЁ вҶ’ рҹҡҗ (pickup only, ends elsewhere) MUST ship the walk/ride-back row. Motion banner = a row leading рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ•/рҹҡӨ."),
    ("2026-06-16", "рҹҡү ARRIVE BANNER STRICT FORMAT вҖ” new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16). Closes the gap where a destination рҹҡү ARRIVE banner's full shape wasn't checked (motion was validated by _validate_motion_row; the вҶ’hotel closer by _CLOSER_TRAIN_RE). Per Motion Rule В§3b + Icon Order В§4 row 4: 'рҹҡү ARRIVE {station}: рҹҡ¶ N min В· рҹҡ• M min вҶ’ {first stop}'. New check: every .arrive-first div NOT ending in 'вҶ’ hotel' (i.e. a destination arrival) must carry the station-label+colon, a motion segment (walk[+ride] or ride-only), then 'вҶ’ {first stop}'. Presence stays a warn (no-transfer days legitimately omit it)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "NO-WIKIPEDIA SENTINEL NOT ABUSABLE вҖ” new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16: the sentinel was being abused). Links.html В§5 omits the рҹ“– row ONLY when no substantive English article exists. Abuse pattern: a dedicated English article DOES exist but a <!-- no-wikipedia: --> sentinel was used to dodge the В§3 h1-name-match gate вҖ” the reason text itself admits it (Quebec City: 'English Wikipedia article title is \"Plains of Abraham\" вҖ” French name used in guide'). New check (text-only, no network) flags sentinels whose reason concedes a usable EN article ('english wikipedia article title is', 'EN article \"вҖҰ\" exists', 'wikipedia article title is \"', 'closest is {Article}'); 'only a German/French/es article exists' and 'no вҖҰ article' stay legitimate. EXPECTED to fail: Quebec City (5)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TRAIN TIMETABLE dep/arr SPAN ORDER вҖ” new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16, Zurich Rhine Falls timetable). Icon Order and Format.html В§4 row 3 is '{dep time} {station} вҶ’ {arr time} {station}', so the first time-span in a .train-time row is the departure (class=\"dep\") and the second is the arrival (class=\"arr\"). Zurich shipped them inverted (8:07am ZГјrich HB tagged .arr, 8:54am Neuhausen tagged .dep) so the CSS emphasis landed on the wrong time. Dominant convention is dep-first (145 rows) vs 24 inverted (all Zurich). New check: any .train-time row whose first/second dep|arr spans aren't dep,arr hard-fails. EXPECTED to fail: Zurich (24 rows) until the classes are swapped."),
    ("2026-06-24", "HEADS UP вҖ” entry heading must NOT start with вқ—пёҸ (2026-06-24 per Dani). Icon belongs on section title only. Reversed the 2026-06-17 requirement: hard-fail changed from 'must start with вқ—пёҸ' to 'must NOT start with вқ—пёҸ'. CORE RULES (Heads Up - Extra Section.html В§2) updated to remove вқ—пёҸ from entry format. All 37 affected guides stripped of the icon. Venue-name checks updated to parse _heading_body directly (no longer needs to strip a leading вқ—пёҸ)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "рҹҡ« CLOSED DAYS NEVER STACKED вҖ” new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16: 'рҹҡ« Closed Saturday / рҹҡ« Closed Sunday вҖ” this needs to fail'). Icon Order and Format.html В§2 Pos 3 + the рҹҸӣ note state multiple closed days collapse into ONE рҹҡ« row (range 'вҖ“' or '&'), never stacked. The existing рҹҡ« ROW FORMAT check validated each рҹҡ« div independently and the inside-box order check gives рҹҡ« a single rank (equal rank passes), so 2+ stacked рҹҡ« rows shipped silently. New check counts рҹҡ«-led rows per operational box (reuses the inside-box order box-walk); >1 in a box hard-fails. EXPECTED to fail: Big Island, Bordeaux, Chicago, Montevideo, Virgin Islands, Zurich (collapse each pair to one '& '/range row)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TOURS вҖ” negative-finding line must be the fixed canonical wording (Tours - Extra Section.html В§5+В§8, added this session at Dani's direction). When a platform group ships no рҹ“… tour, its .entry-body line must read exactly 'No qualifying tours on [Platform] in [City].'; whole-section-empty reads 'No qualifying tours in [City].'. Free-form variants (e.g. Lille's 'No qualifying open-group tours on TripAdvisor Experiences for Lille during this build.') hard-fail. Check scans .entry-body blocks in #tours that contain no рҹ“… and matches the text against the canonical regex. CORE RULES edited + checksums regenerated + doc_workshop_validator clean."),
    ("2026-06-16", "FOOD DELIVERY вҖ” link text must be the bare DOMAIN, not the platform name (Dani 2026-06-16: a `Uber Eats`вҶ’ubereats.com name-as-link-text entry must fail). The platform name is the .extras-sub heading; the transit-box link row shows the domain (e.g. 'ubereats.com', 'deliveroo.fr'). New check T9c: every <a> text in #food-delivery must match a domain pattern (no spaces, dotted TLD, optional path). Dominant convention 255 domain link-texts vs 22 guides showing the name. NOTE: Food Delivery - Extra Section.html В§2 entry-format text is vague ('[Food App] / [Food Delivery App]') вҖ” a rule-doc clarification is parked in the To-Do (Rules for Update). EXPECTED to fail: 22 guides incl. Geneva, Rome, Florence, Los Angeles, Scottsdale, Stockholm, Dubai."),
    ("2026-06-16", "HEADS UP вҖ” note row вҶі-prefix HARD-FAIL RESTORED. Heads Up В§2 specifies the note line as `вҶі [Note]`; the 2026-06-10 entry claims вҶі enforcement was added for the Heads Up note, but the live check had no вҶі requirement (lost in a later edit) and 0 of 32 Heads-Up guides carry it. Re-added: the note row (first body row in the .transit-box, not the Workaround row) must start with вҶі. Length/capitalisation checks strip the вҶі prefix before counting (вҶі U+21B3 is outside _CG_ICON_RE, so the emoji check is unaffected). EXPECTED: all 32 Heads-Up guides fail until each note row gains its вҶі."),
    ("2026-06-16", "INSIDE-BOX ICON ORDER check RESTORED (the 2026-06-16 element-order rewrite removed the '(C)/(D)/(E) intra-row order checks', so box rows could ship in any order). Per Icon Order and Format.html В§2 the in-box order is fixed: рҹҺҹ=1 В· рҹҸӣ/вҸі=2 В· рҹҡ«=3 В· рҹ•җ/вҸ°=4 В· рҹҶ“/рҹ’ө=5 В· вҡ пёҸ=6 В· рҹ“Қ=7, and ranks must be non-decreasing down the box. ONLY glyphs В§2 lists for inside the box are ranked; the `рҹҺ« book at` row (Stops Structure В§3c documents it for TRAIN DAYS only вҖ” its in-box position is undefined) and the guided-tour `рҹ“…` lead are left UNRANKED so the legitimate trailing-book-at pattern (Boston/Alaska/Cayman/Curacao) is not penalised. Genuine violations (e.g. a вҡ пёҸ caveat placed above the рҹҸӣ hours instead of at pos 6) are flagged."),
    ("2026-06-16", "YELLOW-BOX + BARE OPERATIONAL ROWS HARD-FAILS added (restores enforcement the 2026-06-16 element-order rewrite explicitly deferred вҖ” 'not enforced here yet, Istanbul/Palm Desert'). TWO checks: (1) every stop-block must carry an operational box (рҹ“Қ-led .tour-box for no-ticket stops, рҹҺҹ-led .ticket-box for ticketed) вҖ” a stop with NO box = 'yellow box missing'; (2) no logistics row sits OUTSIDE the box вҖ” the full inside-box glyph set рҹҸӣ/рҹҸӣпёҸ hours В· вҸі duration В· рҹҡ« closed В· рҹ•җ/вҸ° time В· рҹҶ“/рҹ’ө cost В· вҡ пёҸ note В· рҹ“Қ address must live INSIDE the box. Both strip box subtrees via _strip_balanced_div first; the glyph must LEAD its row (immediately after a <div> open) so emojis in вҶі prose never match. Caught visually by Dani 2026-06-16: Bali Tegallalang / Mount Batur / Uluwatu (bare рҹҸӣ/вҸ°/вҡ пёҸ/рҹ“Қ, several with no box at all). The pre-existing 'guided stop has no stop-level рҹ“Қ' check only covered guided stops; these cover self / ticket / no-box stops too. EXPECTED: Bali fails (6 no-box + 7 bare-row stops) until the rows are wrapped in a box."),
    ("2026-07-05", "FINAL GATE вҖ” SAFETY GUIDE per-guide direct check. New hard-fail in the FINAL GATE: reads Safety-Guide.html directly and confirms a city-row href points to THIS guide's folder (class=\"city-row\" href=\"../Guides/{City}/\"). Fails ONLY the guide whose city is absent вҖ” the prior fleet-level validate_safety_guide.py subprocess would fail ALL guide validations whenever any city was missing, not just the offending guide's own validation. The direct check is faster, per-guide scoped, and gives a precise fix instruction (which section, which href). Skipped in published-only/CI mode where Safety-Guide.html may not be present."),
    ("2026-07-05", "MULTI-FILE CLI SUPPORT. validate_itinerary.py now accepts one or more file arguments (python3 validate_itinerary.py a.html b.html вҖҰ). Each file is validated in sequence with a separator banner; exit code is 1 if ANY file fails. Previously only sys.argv[1] was processed вҖ” passing multiple files silently ignored everything after the first, causing bulk runs to miss failures in non-first guides (e.g. Bora Bora's 3 failures were invisible when passed as the 6th argument after KrakГіw)."),
    ("2026-07-05", "рҹҸЁ PICKUP ROW BANNED IN STOP-BLOCK TICKET BOXES. New hard-fail: рҹҸЁ вҶ” рҹҡҗ / рҹҸЁ вҶ’ рҹҡҗ / рҹҸЁ вҶҗ рҹҡҗ must never appear inside a stop-block ticket-box. These hotel-pickup rows belong ONLY in Tours section entries (under a рҹ“… heading, Icon Order and Format.html В§2 Tours table). The В§2 inside-box table (Pos 1вҖ“7) has no рҹҡҗ row; a crib fabricated the row in Bora Bora's 'Shark & Ray Lagoon Snorkel Cruise' stop and it passed because the validator only checked order (рҹҡҗ is unranked). Companion fix: row removed from bora-bora_v1.html."),
    ("2026-07-05", "рҹ“Қ ROW CLASS HARD-FAIL added вҖ” every рҹ“Қ address row inside a stop block must carry class=\"stop-row\". A bare classless <div>рҹ“Қ has no matching CSS rule and renders with browser-default block spacing (same defect as the вҶі/рҹ“– class gap caught 2026-06-16). The gap allowed Bora Bora to ship four bare <div>рҹ“Қ rows that passed every other check. New check: any <div> with NO class attribute leading with рҹ“Қ is a hard-fail. Companion fix: all four bare рҹ“Қ rows in bora-bora_v1.html corrected to <div class=\"stop-row\">рҹ“Қ."),
    ("2026-06-16", "вҶі / рҹ“– ROW CLASS HARD-FAIL added вҖ” the вҶі description row and рҹ“– Wikipedia row must carry class=\"stop-row\". Non-canonical classes (Aix-en-Provence shipped stop-desc / stop-wiki) have NO CSS rule, so the rows render with browser-default block margins and the gap before the operational box balloons (caught visually by Dani 2026-06-16, Aix HГҙtel de Caumont). The validator previously had no class check on these rows, so the drift shipped silently. New check flags any <div class=\"вҖҰ\">вҶі or рҹ“– whose class tokens omit `stop-row`; bare class-less box-internal rows (Day Trips transit-box <div>вҶі) are not matched. EXPECTED: Aix fails until its 9 stop-desc + 7 stop-wiki rows are renamed to stop-row."),
    ("2026-06-16", "IN-CITY DAY-CARD SUFFIX CHECK вҖ” no longer false-positives on em-dashes that are part of a real stop name. The check flagged ANY em-dash `вҖ”` in a non-рҹҺ’/non-train overview day-title as a 'city suffix' вҖ” a rule written for the retired рҹҺ’ format. Post-2026-06-16 in-city cards are `Day N вҖ“ Stop1 В· Stop2 В· вҖҰ`, and stop names legitimately contain em-dashes (Lima 'MATE вҖ” Museo Mario Testino', Lucerne 'Mount Pilatus вҖ” Golden Round Trip', Marrakech 'Mellah вҖ” Jewish Quarter', Porto 'Douro River вҖ” Six Bridges Cruise'). Now: strip the 'Day N вҖ“' prefix, split the stop list on ' В· ', and flag an em-dash segment ONLY when it matches no day-block stop name (substring either direction, mirroring the name-sync check). A genuine stray ` вҖ” City` suffix (matching no stop) is still caught. No guide HTML touched."),
    ("2026-06-16", "DAY-HEADER + OVERVIEW TRAIN-DAY SYNC вҖ” two checks brought into line with the 2026-06-16 en-dash convention (both had hard-failed every correctly-built train/coach guide). (A) DAY-HEADER locked patterns: the Train Day / Guided Coach patterns required an em-dash `вҖ”` after 'Day N' (`^Day \\d+ вҖ” Train Day вҖ” вҖҰ`), but all 24 shipped train/coach guides вҖ” and the overview-day-title convention adopted 2026-06-16 вҖ” use the en-dash `вҖ“` there. Patterns now accept `[вҖ“вҖ”]` after 'Day N' (Train-Day destination separator stays flexible too). (B) TRIP OVERVIEW stop-count sync: the inline-stops parser grabbed the text after the en-dash even for Train Day cards, turning the 'рҹҡҶ Train Day вҖ” {Destination}' label into a phantom 1-entry stop list and reporting a count mismatch against the 2-stop day-block. Parser now leaves stops='' when the title contains 'Train Day' (documented intent: Train Day cards carry no inline stop list; the count/name sync skips them). Guided Coach overview cards DO list real stops and are unchanged. No guide HTML touched вҖ” the guides were correct; the checks were stale."),
    ("2026-06-16", "STOP-BLOCK CANONICAL ELEMENT ORDER вҖ” corrected (replaces the backwards checks added earlier today). The earlier pass had the order INVERTED vs Stops Structure.html В§3a/В§3b: it required the .ticket-box BEFORE the вҶі description and forbade the non-guided .tour-box вҖ” but В§3a/В§3b put вҶі (Pos 1) and рҹ“– (Pos 2) FIRST, outside the box, then the operational box (рҹҺҹ-led .ticket-box for ticketed stops, or the canonical рҹ“Қ-led .tour-box for no-ticket stops), with рҹҸӣ/вҸ°/рҹ“Қ INSIDE it. Those backwards checks hard-failed all 134 correctly-built guides while passing the box-first shape (Capri/Bali). NOW: (A) the operational box (.ticket-box or .tour-box) must FOLLOW the вҶі/рҹ“– rows вҖ” flags the box-before-description shape (Capri, Bali); (B) вҶі (Pos 1) precedes рҹ“– (Pos 2). The рҹ“Қ-led .tour-box is recognised as the valid no-ticket logistics box (per _strip_guided_tour_boxes) and no longer flagged. Removed the inverted (A) ticket-box-first check, the (F) no-non-guided-tour-box check, and the box-stripped (C)/(D)/(E) intra-row order checks. NOTE (deferred): bare operational rows outside any box (Istanbul, Palm Desert) are a separate В§3a deviation, not enforced here yet."),
    ("2026-06-16", "ICON REMOVAL hard-fails added: (1) no emoji before Day N in overview-day-title; (2) no inline emoji before stop names in HTML (CSS ::before emptied); (3) no emoji before overview-title text. All three retired 2026-06-16."),
    ("2026-06-16", "NO-ICON-BEFORE checks added: (1) overview-day-title hard-fail when text does not start with 'Day ' (backpack or any icon before day number banned); (2) stop-name inline emoji prefix hard-fail (icon retired from HTML вҖ” CSS ::before is empty). These complement the existing рҹҺ’ HTML-ban check."),
    ("2026-06-16", "PILL LABELS updated вҖ” canonical labels changed: 'Michelin Restaurants' вҶ’ 'Michelin', 'Day Trips by Train' вҶ’ 'Day Trips', 'Stations Near Hotel' вҶ’ 'Train Stations' (overview-extra-link pill text only; section titles unchanged). NEW HARD-FAILS: (1) рҹҺ’ backpack emoji banned from guide HTML (CSS ::before emptied 2026-06-16); (2) Weekly Closures pill must be preceded by <span style='color:#d4b896;padding:0 6px;...'>|</span> separator. Font: guide-style.css now loads Roboto via Google Fonts @import."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TRIP OVERVIEW TITLE: рҹ“Ң icon removed from .overview-title (Dani-approved 2026-06-15). All 134 guides updated. Validator: (1) title check updated вҖ” now requires plain `Trip Overview` with no icon; (2) new hard-fail if рҹ“Ң detected in .overview-title. Trip Overview.html В§h1 updated. Checksum regenerated."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TITLE PAGE COLOR PALETTE вҖ” link-color allowlist updated: .title-page .title-address a #ffffff вҶ’ rgba(255,255,255,0.60) (muted white, palette update 2026-06-15)."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TITLE PAGE COLOR PALETTE (Dani-approved): .title-city вҶ’ #f5e0b8 (warm cream); .title-hotel / .title-address / .title-country вҶ’ rgba(255,255,255,0.60) (muted white). Colors set in guide-style.css and Guide Style.css. Validator: new hard-fail check вҖ” local <style> blocks may not override title color rules with non-canonical values. Buenos Aires local style block removed (now fully covered by guide-style.css)."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TITLE-COUNTRY REQUIRED (Dani-approved): .title-country added to Hotel Banner.html В§1 Entry. Validator updated: (1) expected children list updated from [title-city, title-hotel, title-address] вҶ’ [title-city, title-hotel, title-address, title-country]; (2) new hard-fail check вҖ” .title-country must be present and non-empty (absent or blank = fail). Guide Style.css + guide-style.css updated: .title-page gains position:relative; .title-country added (absolute, right:16px, vertically centered, uppercase, muted white). All 134 live guides updated with correct country names via script. Validator Index.html, Hotel Banner.html В§1 Entry updated."),
    ("2026-06-15", "Second audit pass вҖ” 10 fixes: (1) L11332 comment 'rename day-trips-by-train вҶ’ day-trips' was backwards (rename was day-trips вҶ’ day-trips-by-train, 2026-05-26) and had wrong date (2026-05-02). (2) L11362 check label '13-element sequence' вҶ’ '15-element sequence' (eoi_canonical_order grew to 15 with tours + stations-near-hotel addition). (3) L11370 check label '13 canonical anchor ids' вҶ’ '15 canonical anchor ids'. (4) L11310 eoi_canonical_order inline comment 'ships for CA + AZ trips only' вҶ’ 'ships for CA + AZ + OR trips only'. (5) L11317 comment 'two conditional sections (pickleball, heads-up)' вҶ’ 'four conditional sections (pickleball, heads-up, skip-list, day-trips-by-train)'. (6) L11419 T4 check label '10 universal (1вҖ“9 plus Michelin at #11)' вҶ’ '11 universal (1вҖ“10 plus Michelin at #13)'. (7) T5/T6 position labels: pickleball #9 вҶ’ #12, heads-up #11 вҶ’ #14, T5 comment '#10' вҶ’ '#12', T6 comment '#12' вҶ’ '#14'. (8) T5 comment 'CA + AZ' вҶ’ 'CA + AZ + OR'. (9) L11630 skip-list gate used bare substring 'c in trip_city_text' вҖ” same false-positive risk as 'nice in venice' fixed in Heads Up gate (2026-06-05); fixed to use re.search word-boundary match. (10) L22788 second skip-list city matcher (detailed entry check) also used bare substring; fixed to word-boundary re.search. (11) L12270 _SECTION_IDS for structural </div> balance check was missing 'skip-list' вҖ” 14 entries, should be 15; skip-list section could have unclosed div and structural check would silently skip it."),
    ("2026-06-15", "CHANGELOG display fixed: CHANGELOG[-5:] вҶ’ CHANGELOG[:5] (L24024). Entries are stored newest-first (prepended); -5 slice was showing the 5 oldest entries, not the 5 most recent. Also: L5948 _row_end_re = re.compile(r'</div>') hoisted before both for-loops in INFORMATION ROWS ARE PLAIN TEXT check вҖ” was compiled on every hit of every glyph (compiled inside inner for-m loop body). Now compiled once before the outer 'for glyph' loop as _row_end_re; reference updated from row_end_re to _row_end_re. No behaviour change."),
    ("2026-06-15", "DAY TRIPS вҖ” Island-city ZERO entries hard-fail added (В§ 2.2, 2026-06-15): _ISLAND_CITIES set covers all island guides system-wide (Capri, Corfu, Azores, Madeira, Iceland, Aruba, Bahamas, Barbados, Cayman Islands, Curacao, Puerto Rico, Sint Maarten, Virgin Islands, Big Island, Kauai, Maui, Oahu). Hard-fail if any extras-sub entry exists in Day Trips for an island city. Azores, Madeira, Iceland moved out of _EUROPEAN_GUIDE_CITIES into _ISLAND_CITIES with exemption comments. Rule home: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§ 2.2."),
    ("2026-06-15", "DAY TRIPS вҖ” European-country MIN 5 HARD FAIL added (Dani-approved). New rule home: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§ 4. A guide whose .title-city is in a European country MUST ship вүҘ5 entries in the Day Trips by Train section; below the floor = hard fail. Implemented via a new _EUROPEAN_GUIDE_CITIES set (defined inline next to the check вҖ” editable, commented per-country) keyed off city_text. Existing rules preserved unchanged: В§ 1 'A destination already covered as a Train Day in this guide's itinerary never ships here' (validator: line 16339 Train-Day dedup check, line 17457 destination-conflict check), and the warn-only low-count comment for non-European guides (line 17565). Companion updates same pass: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§ 4, Brain/Reference/Rule Dependencies.html (Day Trips icon card), Brain/Reference/Guide Entry Counts.html В§ 1, Brain/Reference/Validator Index.html вӣІпёҸ DAY TRIPS, core_rules_checksums.json regenerated."),
    ("2026-06-15", "12-part validator audit вҖ” 9 fixes: (1) L330 unused 'import re as _re_wok' removed (re already imported at module level, alias never referenced). (2) L5737-5767 _wr_hours_min_re/_wr_hours_re/_wr_min_re hoisted out of _validate_motion_row and compiled once before the function (were compiled on every call; function called ~hundreds of times per guide run). (3) L8009 _CAP_EXTRA_ICON_RE hoisted out of cappuccino entries loop to before the loop (was compiled on every entry iteration). (4-6) L13039 / L14062 / L14127 / L12743 / L12766 / L12848: 'day-trips' legacy section id replaced with 'day-trips-by-train' in _get_section_html call (Day Trips вҶі length check silently never ran), _DIV_BALANCE_SECTIONS (div-balance check silent), _SECTION_ICON_ALLOWLISTS (icon check silent), required_extras tuple + special-case guard (title + empty checks silent), and _SECTION_ICON_MAP (icon check silent). All 5 Day Trips checks were silently skipped on every current guide since the 2026-05-26 rename. (7) L21868 bare_host_pattern = re.compile() inside nested ticket-link loop inlined to re.match() call (no behaviour change). (8-10) Three redundant 'from urllib.parse import unquote as _uqN' inside validate() removed (L18582 _uq2, L18603 _uq3, L23807 _fg_uq) вҖ” all replaced with the module-level _url_unquote alias. No check logic changed in any fix."),
    ("2026-06-13", "FINAL GATE map-pin check вҖ” added 'Caribbean Map.html' to _fg_map_names (was 6 continent maps: Europe/US/Asia/Africa/Oceania/South America). The 2026-06-13 Travel-Website reorg introduced Caribbean Map.html as a 7th pin target; the 8 island guides (Aruba, Bahamas, Barbados, Cayman Islands, Curacao, Puerto Rico, Sint Maarten, Virgin Islands) are correctly pinned there but were failing the FINAL GATE because the validator did not scan it. No guide changed вҖ” gate now scans all 7 maps. Companion updates same pass: guide_tools.py _check_guide_pinned, Navigation.html В§5, Ship Checklist.html В§11, CLAUDE.md DriftyCat."),
    ("2026-06-10", "IN-HOTEL FORMAT rule added to Michelin Restaurants - Extra Section.html В§3 and Cappuccino - Extra Section.html В§3 (mirrors RNH В§5a): when the restaurant/cafГ© is inside the guide hotel, use 'рҹҸЁ In the hotel В· [Floor]' with no рҹ“Қ or motion row; Michelin in-hotel entry comes first within its star tier (ride time = 0); Cappuccino in-hotel entry comes first in the section. Validator already handles this via the рҹҸЁ sentinel (ride_time = 0 for check-D)."),
    ("2026-06-10", "Michelin check J (banned rows) updated: рҹҸӣ/рҹҡ« ban now exempts in-hotel entries (В§3a legitimately carries рҹҸӣ hours and рҹҡ« closed rows); ban still applies to all В§3b standard entries. La Palme d'Or Michelin entry hours fixed: en-dash вҶ’ space-dash-space per рҹҸӣ separator rule."),
    ("2026-06-10", "вҶі prefix enforcement added to all description rows: Shows (was рҹ—’), Day Trips (was рҹ—һпёҸ), Local Tastes, Getting Around tram, Heads Up note, Stations Near Hotel, Downtown Restaurants, Pickleball вҖ” all description rows must start with вҶі; char-limit checks strip вҶі before counting. Day Trips _DT_BOX_ALLOWED updated to ('вҶі', 'рҹҺ«'). RNH В§5a, В§5b, Michelin В§3a, В§3b, Cappuccino В§3a, В§3b: description rows must start with вҶі; char-limit checks strip вҶі before counting (content after вҶі вүӨ80). Michelin and Cappuccino now branch on in-hotel vs standard entry: in-hotel (В§a) bans рҹ“Қ and рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ•, requires рҹҸЁ In the hotel В· [Floor] and рҹҸӣ rows; standard (В§b) keeps existing address/motion checks. Cappuccino hotel entry excluded from minimum-5 count. La Palme d\'Or Michelin entry in Cannes updated to В§3a format (removed рҹ“Қ, added floor + hours + closed rows)."),
    ("2026-06-10", "STOP DESCRIPTION вҖ” рҹ“’ retired, вҶі now required: stop description row (outside the blue box, Pos 1 per Icon Order and Format.html В§2) switches from рҹ“’ to вҶі, matching all extra-section description rows. Validator: STOP DESCRIPTION LENGTH, ROW FORMAT (no links), and ROW FORMAT (no annotations) checks updated from рҹ“’ pattern to вҶі pattern. Tour-box containment check updated: 'рҹ“’ inside tour-box' вҶ’ 'вҶі inside tour-box'. Shows Cleanliness Check 402 tombstoned (рҹ“’ negative-finding row retired вҖ” negative-finding uses extras-empty class). Guide Style.css and Validator Index updated. Rule files (Icon Order and Format.html, Stops Structure.html) already showed вҶі вҖ” no change needed."),
    ("2026-06-10", "Michelin check-D in-hotel sentinel: 'рҹҸЁ In the hotel' motion row is now recognised as ride_time = 0 for the within-tier sort key (the restaurant is physically inside the guide hotel). The zero-time hard-fail in _validate_motion_row correctly bans 'рҹҡ• 0 min' from appearing in guides, but check D previously treated any missing рҹҡ• time as -1 (absent), causing a spurious sort-order failure. Cannes: La Palme d'Or at HГҙtel Martinez updated from 'рҹҡ¶ 0 min В· рҹҡ• 0 min' to 'рҹҸЁ In the hotel'."),
    ("2026-06-11", "CHINA RAIL вҖ” _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS + omio-required exemption (Dani, Proposal E): added 12306.cn (China Railway national booking platform) to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS вҖ” Omio has no China coverage, so it was the only valid operator missing from the allowlist. Added _OMIO_EXEMPT_CITIES set (mainland Chinese cities: chongqing, beijing, shanghai, and 17 others) and gated the omio-required check on the guide city not being in that set. CORE RULES companion: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§2 now includes the Omio coverage exception paragraph. No check logic changed for non-China guides."),
    ("2026-06-11", "LINK_COLOR_ALLOWLIST вҖ” corrected stale hex values for theme-coral, theme-sage, and theme-green toolbar entries. Coral was #1c8a99 (wrong: that is --c-gettingaround-border / teal); corrected to #c85a54 (--c-coral-border). Sage was #8b3520 (wrong: that is --c-closures-border); corrected to #448088 (--c-sage-border). Green was #1c8a99 (wrong); corrected to #5a74c4 (--c-shows-border). All three were introduced with wrong variable mappings at some point after the 2026-05-29 allowlist expansion; the CSS in guide-style.css was always correct. No rule change вҖ” allowlist now matches the deployed CSS. CHANGELOG label/comment only; check logic unchanged."),
    ("2026-06-10", "рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• ZERO-TIME HARD FAIL added to _validate_motion_row: a travel time of 0 min (or 0h / 0h 0min) is never a valid display value вҖ” use actual measured time or omit the row. Enforced in both the N min path (N==0) and the Xh Ymin / Xh path (total==0). Applies to every motion row across all sections."),
    ("2026-06-06", "DAY TRIPS вҖ” Train-Day-destination dedup check added (Dani, cross-check item 21): hard fail when a Day Trips by Train extras-sub city matches any Train Day destination parsed from the guide's day-header divs (same extraction as the destination-вү -guide-city check). Rule home: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html. EXPECTED: guides whose Day Trips section lists their own Train Day destination now fail until the duplicate entry is removed (Dani: guides failing is fine)."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Stops Structure calibration anchor 'В§1 food-street anchor (Rue Mouffetard)' RETIRED вҖ” the market-streets / pedestrian-food-strolls inclusion block was removed from Stops Structure.html В§1b (Dani, cross-check item 7: В§1c markets-of-any-kind exclusion governs without carve-out). The anchor guarded a block that no longer exists."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Skip List.html renamed to Skip List - Extra Section.html (Dani, cross-check item 25 вҖ” file follows the [Section] - Extra Section.html naming). BUILD_STATE_PHASE_5_MAP value + all labels/comments updated; all guides' build_state.md Phase 5 entries updated in the same pass. No check logic changed."),
    ("2026-06-06", "FOOTNOTE TOOLBAR RETIRED (Dani): the footer sharing link is retired for now and must not be used in the guides. Guides/toolbar.js now carries FOOTNOTE_RETIRED = true and never auto-loads footnote.js (loader kept behind the guard for re-enable). TB-9 rewritten: guide loads toolbar.js + no inline footer div + no direct footnote.js script tag. TB-11 rewritten: was footnote.js structure check; now verifies the FOOTNOTE_RETIRED guard is present and true in Guides/toolbar.js. footnote.js stays on disk, unused. Rule updated: Brain/Reference/Toolbar.html В§6 (Retired) + Navigation.html В§1 + Rules for Claude.html В§4 publishing note (approved CORE RULES edit; checksums regenerated)."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Deep-audit decision 3 (Dani): klook.com REMOVED from _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS вҖ” Klook is an attractions/tours aggregator, not a train booking site; any Klook URL (incl. tour pages) passed the Day Trips operator gate. Rail bookings must use the actual operator site."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Deep-audit decision 2 (Dani): рҹ’° CURRENCY FORMAT block RETIRED (trailing-USD label check + non-USD symbol drift-catcher). It cited a Stops Structure price rule that no longer exists; the live rule is DriftyCat zero-money ('no $ вӮ¬ ВЈ ВҘ, no ISO codes вҖ” ever'), already enforced by the global ZERO-CURRENCY check. Both sub-checks could only pass vacuously. Single source of truth: one global check, prices/currency banned everywhere."),
    ("2026-06-10", "STRUCTURAL check added: every extras-section div must have a matching closing </div>. Detected via _walk_balanced_div вҖ” if end_index == len(html) the div was never closed. Covers all 14 section IDs (weekly-closures, tours, cappuccino, restaurants, michelin, downtown, local-tastes, food-delivery, shows, getting-around, stations-near-hotel, day-trips, pickleball, heads-up). A missing </div> nests all downstream sections inside the unclosed one, breaking mobile CSS layout. Hard-fail. 54 guides fixed (42 in prior session + 12 remaining getting-around sections)."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Deep-audit decision 1 (Dani): two always-pass reminder check()s converted to warn() вҖ” Getting Around 'ride app availability confirmed via web search' and Food Delivery 'platform availability confirmed via web search'. An unconditional вң… asserted verification that never happened and inflated the pass count. Now вҡ пёҸ warnings, suppressible via <!-- warn-ok: ride-app-search --> / <!-- warn-ok: food-delivery-search --> once confirmed."),
    ("2026-06-06", "CITATION REFRESH (CORE RULES audit): stale В§ citations corrected in check labels and comments вҖ” Train Day quota checks now cite Day Structure.html В§6 (was Stops Structure.html В§5; the quota rule lives in Day Structure), рҹҺ« train-header row checks + train-modifier comments now cite Stops Structure.html В§3c (was В§5 вҖ” renumbered by the 2026-05-26 file consolidation). No check logic changed вҖ” labels and comments only. Companion: brain_check.py gained check_section_citation_targets() (warn-mode) to catch future В§ renumbering drift."),
    ("2026-06-15", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added elron.ee to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Elron вҖ” Estonia's national rail operator; Tallinn build, covers TallinnвҖ“Tartu, TallinnвҖ“Narva, TallinnвҖ“PГӨrnu, TallinnвҖ“Paldiski lines). Omio covers Estonia, so the 'or omio' suffix stands."),
    ("2026-06-15", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added croatiarailways.hr to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Hrvatske Еҫeljeznice вҖ” Croatia's national rail operator; Split build, covers SplitвҖ“Е ibenikвҖ“KninвҖ“Zagreb main line). Omio covers Croatia, so the 'or omio' suffix stands."),
    ("2026-06-12", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added metlink.org.nz to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Metlink вҖ” Greater Wellington regional rail operator: KДҒpiti / Hutt Valley / Wairarapa lines; Wellington build, same pattern as the gotransit / sunrail / gobrightline additions). Omio covers NZ, so the 'or omio' suffix stands and Wellington is NOT added to _OMIO_EXEMPT_CITIES."),
    ("2026-06-12", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added sz.si / potniski.sz.si / slo-zeleznice.si to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Slovenske Еҫeleznice вҖ” Slovenia's national rail operator; Ljubljana build, same pattern as the gotransit / sunrail additions). Omio covers Slovenia, so the 'or omio' suffix stands."),
    ("2026-06-07", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added gotransit.com to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (GO Transit/Metrolinx вҖ” Ontario regional rail operator, Toronto-Niagara Falls route; Toronto build, same pattern as the 2026-06-06 sunrail/gobrightline addition)"),
    ("2026-06-06", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added sunrail.com + gobrightline.com to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Florida commuter/intercity rail operators вҖ” Orlando build)"),
    ("2026-06-06", "FINAL GATE вҖ” вқ“ OPEN QUESTIONS PARKING GATE added (Dani): at the end of validation the guide hard-fails if To Do List вқ“ Open Questions holds an entry naming this guide's city that is NOT a CORE RULES fix/edit/proposal question (detected by core rules / rules for update / rules for claude tokens). The build crib makes every other call itself and documents it (decisions log / build sentinels) вҖ” вқ“ is reserved for CORE RULES questions only. Scoped per-city so one crib's parked question never blocks another crib's build."),
    ("2026-06-06", "рҹ“Қ HOME-CITY-IN-DISPLAY check вҖ” street-name carve-out (Miami build). The check substring-matched the home city anywhere in the anchor text, so '3251 S Miami Ave В· Coconut Grove' hard-failed for the Miami guide even though the rule (Links.html В§6) bans the redundant city SUFFIX, not street names that contain the city word. Now a word-boundary match that ignores the home-city token when immediately followed by a street suffix (Ave/St/Blvd/Rd/Dr/Way/Ln/Ct/Hwy/Pkwy/Ter/Pl/Sq and long forms). A standalone trailing city ('вҖҰ В· Miami') still fails."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Overview extras sync check B aligned with Trip Overview.html В§3: the вңЁ Claude Inspiration pill is no longer flagged as an orphan when the claude-inspiration div exists (it is not an extras-section by design вҖ” Claude Inspiration - Extra Section.html В§4). Pill stays optional: check A unchanged, guides without the pill still pass. First shipped on Corfu v1."),
    ("2026-06-05", "рҹҡӨ CAR-FREE CITY RIDE GLYPH added (Dani-approved, Option B). New CORE RULES rule: cities with no road network (CAR_FREE_CITIES = {'venice'}) use рҹҡӨ (water-taxi) instead of рҹҡ• in every motion banner + from-hotel row (Motion Rule.html В§1, Icon Order and Format.html В§2 row 8f). Validator: a single enforcement check runs on raw html (car-free вҶ’ рҹҡ• must not appear outside Getting Around; road city вҶ’ рҹҡӨ must not appear at all), then рҹҡӨ is normalised to рҹҡ• so every existing ride check вҖ” closer format, RNH/Cappuccino/Stations motion rows, Michelin check-D ride parse + within-tier sort, Tours рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• вҖ” validates рҹҡӨ with the identical format/time/order rules as рҹҡ• (no per-check edits needed). Migrated Venice (25 motion rows рҹҡ•вҶ’рҹҡӨ; Getting Around 'рҹҡ• Ride Apps' heading retained). Verified Venice 0 failures."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Michelin check-D ride parser extended to read Motion-Rule time formats. The old parser ('рҹҡ•[^0-9]{0,15}(\\d+)\\s*min') only recognised the 'N min' form and reported any hours-format ride ('рҹҡ• 1h 7min') as a missing рҹҡ• time вҖ” failing check D on cross-city guides whose Michelin venues are вүҘ60 min away (surfaced on Palo Alto: hotel in Mountain View, all 5 starred venues in San Francisco). Now parses 'N min', 'Xh Ymin' and 'Xh' to total minutes, matching Motion Rule В§1's enforced format. Working-surface fix during the item-17 backfill; no rule change. Verified Palo Alto 685/0."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Links В§3 staleness reconciled (To Do List item 19, Dani). Dead _log_entry_age helper removed вҖ” the 30вҖ“90-day WARN tier was retired 2026-05-27 (a logged PASS now permanently suppresses the warning, no age expiry), so the helper was never called. Links.html В§3 rule text updated to match: 'Logged PASS вҶ’ green (permanent, no expiry); Missing/non-PASS вҶ’ WARN'. No behavior change вҖ” helper was already dead."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Michelin within-tier order FLIPPED alphabetical вҶ’ closest-to-hotel first by рҹҡ• ride time (To Do List item 17, Dani). Michelin entries now carry a рҹҡ¶ N min В· рҹҡ• N min вҶ’ hotel motion row (Michelin Restaurants - Extra Section.html В§3 updated); check D parses the рҹҡ• minutes and enforces non-decreasing order within each star tier, hard-failing when a tier is out of order OR any entry lacks the рҹҡ• from-hotel time. FIXED a latent parser bug: the audit block read stars from .entry-body row 1, but Style A (locked 2026-05-19) puts вӯҗ+name on the .extras-sub heading вҖ” so entries_audit was ALWAYS empty on current guides and checks B/D/E/F/H/I/J/L/N ran vacuously. Now reads stars from the preceding .extras-sub heading; cuisine region = box-startвҶ’рҹ“Қ. J banned-rows updated: рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• removed from the ban (now required), рҹҸӣ/рҹҡ« still banned. EXPECTED: all 50 guides with a Michelin section now fail check D until the рҹҡ• from-hotel times are backfilled per entry."),
    ("2026-06-05", "A4 follow-up (Dani) вҖ” NEW global hard-fail: any bare вқ— (U+2757 not followed by U+FE0F) anywhere in a guide fails (regex вқ—(?!пёҸ) over full html, including comments). Guarantees every вқ— вҖ” pill, section title, and each entry marker вҖ” uses +VS16; bare entries previously slipped through (entry parser startswith('вқ—пёҸ ') silently skipped them). Caught + fixed a bare вқ— in Berlin's '<!-- вқ— HEADS UP -->' build comment. All guides re-swept: zero bare вқ— remain."),
    ("2026-06-05", "A4 (To Do List) вҖ” Heads Up icon glyph unified to +VS16 per Dani. Title check (_cg_title_exact) flipped from bare 'вқ— Heads Up' to 'вқ—пёҸ Heads Up' (U+2757+FE0F); comment + fail messages updated; pill expected-label map and icon-map check display string updated to +VS16 (pill compare already FE0F-normalized, so cosmetic). Entry parser unchanged (already required +VS16). CORE RULES docs (Trip Overview pill, Heads Up <h1> title) and all 16 guides carrying a Heads Up section migrated bareвҶ’+VS16; re-validated вҖ” title check passes, no Heads-Up-related failures introduced."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Deep-audit fix pass (Lane 1-5, non-CORE-RULES items). LANE 1: closer-format + logistic-row-parenthetical checks now match div bodies tolerant of inline markup (the old [^<]* grab skipped any row with a <strong>/<a>, a false negative); STOP_TYPE_ICONS gained bare рҹҺҹ; _day_idx prefix branch guarded to len>=3; pill-label compare FE0F-normalized; closer-format LABEL corrected to match regex+rule (ride-only рҹҡ• valid when walk>40min). LANE 2: T_NEW5 relaxed to any lowercase theme token (В§2 'choose freely'); NEW T_NEW8 вҖ” CI title icon must not reuse a section-header icon (В§2). (CI pill-label enforcement deliberately NOT added вҖ” unresolved fixed-vs-free contradiction parked in To Do List.) LANE 3: removed 2 dead always-pass checks (Day Trips 'always allowed', Day Trips 'section present'); collapsed 41 mislabeled Heads-Up 'section absent' placeholders (fired on spec-file-unreadable) to one honest line. LANE 5: Count Reference.html -> Guide Entry Counts.html in all check labels/comments. Verified via golden-master harness вҖ” only intended output changes, no new guide failures."),
    ("2026-06-05", "REMOVED idx-coverage-all check (the 'all guide folders listed in Guides-Index.html' check / former Check B) вҖ” it scanned every Guides/ folder and hard-failed the guide under test whenever ANY sibling guide's HTML was absent from Guides-Index.html. With multiple cribs building guides concurrently, a sibling's in-progress or not-yet-indexed build is routinely present, so this check cross-failed essentially every guide for a condition the current guide cannot control. Index coverage is now fully self-scoped: idx-coverage-self (Check A, retained) verifies THIS guide is indexed, and guide_tools.py ship gate (_check_guide_indexed) enforces it at ship time per crib (per the 2026-06-02 'each crib checks only its own guide' decision). Empty _build-only folders never triggered the removed check (no top-level HTML); the trigger was always a concurrent shipped-but-unindexed sibling. Validator Index.html updated."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Robustness fix (validator audit): results.clear() added at the top of validate() вҖ” the module-level results list was never reset, so a second in-process validate() call would accumulate the prior run's entries and double-count the pass/fail/warn tally. Harmless under CLI single-call use; closes the latent bug for any future import/reuse. No check logic changed; _warn_ok_tags already reset at top of validate()."),
    ("2026-06-02", "Validator fix: _idx_hrefs uses dest-card class (was overview-day вҖ” guides_index was redesigned to use dest-card); map lookup now checks Trip-Essentials/Maps/ first; _INDEX_EXCLUDED_GUIDES emptied (Copenhagen + Edinburgh shipped)."),
    ("2026-06-02", "MAP PIN check added: FAIL if the guide's city name is not present as a PINS entry in Trip-Essentials/Europe Map.html or Trip-Essentials/US Map.html. Enforces Navigation.html В§ 5 step 5 (map pin rule added 2026-06-02). Check runs after the GUIDES INDEX coverage check. Companion changes: guide_tools.py ship gate (_check_guide_pinned), CLAUDE.md DriftyCat, Navigation.html В§ 5, Ship Checklist.html В§ 11, Validator Index.html."),
    ("2026-06-02", "BUILD_STATE_PHASE_1: 'Capabilities' renamed to 'Connectors.html' вҖ” guide_tools.py init already emitted 'Connectors.html'; validator was still checking the old name, causing a Phase 1 fail on any guide built via init. All existing build_state.md files updated in the same pass."),
    ("2026-06-02", "Phase 1+2 early exit: _bs_phase_check now returns bool; if Phase 1 or Phase 2 unchecked, validator halts immediately with a loud banner listing which files are missing/unchecked and exits with code 2. Running 500+ checks on invented-format HTML is noise вҖ” halt forces the reads first."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Editorial drift words banned from guide content and CORE RULES note spans: 'vibe', 'contactless', 'fastest way', 'worth the trip/a visit/it', 'worth crossing' added to _HEDGE_PATTERNS (hard-fail in shipped guides); 'vibe', 'worth', 'ticket info', 'kind of experience', 'character' added to _CR_NOTE_BANNED_WORDS (hard-fail in CORE RULES <span class=\"note\"> annotations). Companion rule edits: 'kind of experience' removed from Getting Around, Icon Order, Tours; 'ticket info' removed from Getting Around, Icon Order; 'vibe', 'and character', 'why it worth the trip', 'the surprise', 'route/stops/line details' removed from all description note spans across Pickleball, Downtown Restaurants, Heads Up, Day Trips by Train. London metro description to be fixed (contactless + fastest way)."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Local Tastes calibration anchor updated: 'В§2 Google Maps link anchor' вҶ’ 'В§2 location anchor' (needle 'Google Maps' вҶ’ 'goes to its location') вҖ” Local Tastes spec text changed from 'is a Google Maps link' to 'goes to its location' as part of Maps/Link word ban."),
    ("2026-05-27", '"Map"/"Maps" bare visible text banned globally вҖ” any text node containing the word Map or Maps (case-insensitive, singular or plural) now hard-fails. Extends the existing <a>Maps</a> link-text check to cover all visible text drift (e.g. "Address [Maps]"). Per Icon Order and Format.html row 7 вҖ” address IS the link, the word Map/Maps never appears as guide text.'),
    ("2026-05-08", "Initial validator вҖ” core structure, stop/section checks"),
    ("2026-05-08", "STANDING ORDER added: write check before fixing guide"),
    ("2026-05-18", "Tram section checks: operator link required when tram present, forbidden when absent"),
    ("2026-05-18", "Transit-box check added for Getting Around extra section"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Heads Up: flipped check вҖ” entries must use .transit-box, bare divs now fail"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Heads Up: rewrote row collector using _walk_balanced_div (position-based walk)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ“… rows: em-dash between tour name and operator now fails (must use В·)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Time format: clock notation (2h00, 1h25) now fails вҖ” must use English (2 hrs, 1 hr 25 min)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "CHANGELOG block added вҖ” embedded at top of file, prints last 5 entries at end of every run"),
    ("2026-05-19", "CSS check: text-transform:lowercase on <a> must have .overview-day override (navigation anchors exempt)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Postal/zip codes banned from address link display text вҖ” 600+ links cleaned across all guides"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Removed postal-code-required checks from Downtown Restaurants, Shows, Michelin, Hotel Banner"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ“… encapsulation check: operatorВ·ratingВ·reviews must be inside <a> tag, not trailing after </a>"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Transit-box stubs cleaned: MRT./London Underground. placeholder divs + Metro planned: notes removed"),
    ("2026-05-19", "CSS check flipped: text-transform:lowercase on <a> is now banned (was: required with exemptions)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Stale stamp check: FAIL if guide edited after last validation stamp (mtime > stamp + 60s grace) вҖ” REMOVED 2026-05-26 at Dani's request; fired on every edit, noise without value."),
    ("2026-05-19", "Title drift check: <title> must be plain place name вҖ” no year/month/season/duration/'Travel Guide'"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Title/index sync check: <title> must exactly match Guides-Index.html entry (number prefix stripped)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҸӣпёҸ strict regex extended: optional trailing parenthetical qualifier allowed (Option B consolidated hours)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "3+ consecutive рҹҸӣпёҸ rows check: must be consolidated to Option B format вҖ” hard fail"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Logistic-row parenthetical check: рҹҸӣпёҸ rows excluded (Option B qualifier allowed; checked by _HRS_STRICT_RE)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Visible-text parentheses check: рҹҸӣпёҸ rows stripped before scan (Option B trailing qualifier exempt)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ“… link text strict format: must end 'В· N.N[вҳ…вӯҗ] В· N+ reviews' with вүҘ2 В· separators"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Food review link format: link text must be 'N.Nвӯҗ В· N+ reviews' вҖ” no extra text, вӯҗ required"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Domain link check flipped: bare-domain link text must be all-lowercase in source (not title-cased)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Tour link bold: only tour name is bold вҖ” CSS .tour-box a / .ticket-box a set to normal weight, <strong> wraps name only"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ“… link <strong> check: tour name inside <a> must be wrapped in <strong> вҖ” bare text fails"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ“… link text format regex fix: changed [^<]+ to .*? + tag-strip so <strong>-wrapped names are actually checked"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҺҹ ticket-box link <strong> check: venue name (first В· segment) must be in <strong>, rest plain text"),
    ("2026-05-19", "вҳ… replaced with вӯҗ in all tour/ticket <a> links вҖ” consistent native emoji color, no CSS needed"),
    ("2026-05-19", "ticket_link_re bare-host check: fixed [^<]+ вҶ’ (.*?) + tag-strip so <strong>-wrapped text is evaluated"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Tour/ticket link format check updated: вҳ… no longer accepted, only вӯҗ (unified emoji star)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Pickleball state detection: Pattern C added вҖ” state code at end of address with no ZIP ('City ST')"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Pickleball walk cap: raised from 25 to 28 min hard cap (rules allow a few minutes over)"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҸӣ hours separator: en-dash (вҖ“) banned in day and time ranges вҖ” use space-hyphen-space ' - ' exclusively"),
    ("2026-05-19", "вӯҗ star spacing: space required before вӯҗ in ratings вҖ” '4.8 вӯҗ' not '4.8вӯҗ'; all rating regexes updated"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Style A spacing lock: extras-sub padding-bottom=0 and body-box padding-top=0 enforced via CSS drift sentinels; stale '4px' anchor updated"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҚ® Local Tastes L: рҹ“Қ row must contain only <a> links separated by В· вҖ” any text after </a> beyond the separator now fails"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҡҠ Metro A: рҹҡҠ section containing tram negative-finding text now fails вҖ” tram content belongs in рҹҡҺ Tram section only"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҡҠ Metro B: when рҹҡҠ Metro ships with real content, operator website link required in transit-box last row"),
    ("2026-05-19", "Link styling C: inline style='text-decoration:...' on <a> tags now fails вҖ” link styling is CSS-only"),
    ("2026-05-19", "CORE RULES content: banned annotation phrases ('вҶ’ heading row', 'first/last row of body box', 'body box') now fail вҖ” layout notes are not rules"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹҡ« row capitalisation: 'closed' (lowercase) now fails вҖ” must be 'Closed' with capital C"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ—“пёҸ Weekly Closures: 'Closed' must be capitalised вҖ” flipped WC-X1 and format regex to require capital C, fail lowercase"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ—“пёҸ Weekly Closures: separator changed from em-dash to В· вҖ” format is now 'Category В· Closed Day'; validator and all guides updated"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ—“пёҸ Weekly Closures: WC-X4 extended вҖ” all words in category name must be title-cased, not just the first; '&' exempt"),
    ("2026-05-19", "рҹ“Қ Maps link: home city in display text now fails вҖ” city belongs in URL query only; different city allowed for out-of-city stops"),
    ("2026-05-20", "вӯҗ star spacing REVERSED (supersedes 2026-05-19): rating is tight N.Nвӯҗ, no space before вӯҗ вҖ” '4.8вӯҗ' not '4.8 вӯҗ'. New global check fails any decimal rating with a space before the star. Rules (venue review-link, Tours, Tickets) all use tight; newest rule prevails."),
    ("2026-05-20", "рҹ“… Tours: added as Extras section (after Weekly Closures) вҖ” section enums, entry-format / rating-bar / per-platform-minimum checks. _TOURS_MINIMUM_EXEMPT rollout exemption removed 2026-06-02 (all guides fixed)"),
    ("2026-05-21", "рҹҺҹ Tours flat-format check: hard FAIL if any .tour-box wrapper found inside #tours extras-section вҖ” Tours entries must use flat Iceland layout (plain divs in .entry-body); nested .tour-box = double background + retired format"),
    ("2026-05-23", "Getting Around В§2b tram description row enforced вҖ” first row of tram transit-box must be вүӨ80 char service description, not the template line; hard fail when missing"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Getting Around В§2b tram description row cap raised to вүӨ160 chars (2 lines max) вҖ” rule updated in Icon Order and Format.html В§3"),
    ("2026-05-23", "warn-ok sentinel system: every вҡ пёҸ warning now instructs guide to add <!-- warn-ok: TAG reason --> comment to document why it is acceptable; tram-not-planned check added вҖ” warns when Getting Around lists рҹҡҺ Tram but no tram rows in itinerary"),
    ("2026-05-24", "вӣІпёҸ Day Trips by Train рҹҺ« aggregator guard: Viator/GYG/TripAdvisor links in Day Trips рҹҺ« rows now fail вҖ” booking must go to the transport operator (train/bus/transfer site), not a guided-tour aggregator (Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§2)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҡ— Food Delivery transit-box link-only tightened: description text mixed into the URL link div now fails вҖ” link div must contain ONLY <a href=...>; no surrounding prose (Food Delivery - Extra Section.html В§2)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҡ• Getting Around per-app ride-app transit-box link-only check вҖ” each рҹҡ• extras-sub transit-box must have exactly 1 child div (operator link); description rows fail (В§1b gap: prior checks only matched 'Ride App' heading, missed per-app рҹҡ• Grab / рҹҡ• Gojek format)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Getting Around stale code audit: (1) tram description check comment + error message corrected from 'вүӨ80 chars' to 'вүӨ160 chars' (cap was raised 2026-05-24 but comment was not updated); (2) retired comment claiming 'description div BETWEEN heading and transit-box is by design' corrected вҖ” that intermediate format was retired 2026-05-24 and the gap check (added 2026-05-25) explicitly bans it; (3) two stale old-format check labels that said 'description (вүӨ80 chars)' updated to reflect no-description rule (В§1b)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡ• Getting Around intermediate description div gap fixed вҖ” description div placed BETWEEN the рҹҡ• extras-sub and the transit-box was invisible to the transit-box child-div count check; new gap check strips comments and hard-fails on any non-whitespace <div> in that space (В§1b: no description row)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "вҳ• Cappuccino audit вҖ” two new checks added: (F) annotation leakage ([UPDATE]/[CHECK]/рҹ”ҙ/[TBD] etc. in heading or entry body hard-fail, same pattern as DR/RNH/Shows); (G) duplicate cafГ© names within the section (copy-paste error, same pattern as DR/WC/Michelin). Coverage fixed: 'maximum 5' claim removed (CORE RULES has no maximum cap); 'No build annotations' coverage item now accurately reflects enforcement (was false-yes before this session)."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel audit вҖ” entry count check added: 3+ entries now hard-fail per В§ 2 (one local/regional + one high-speed; same station = 1 combined entry; Coverage said 'yes' but no check existed вҖ” false-yes fixed). Coverage updated: added 'bus station entries' and 'рҹҺҹ aggregator booking link' items that were enforced in validator but not documented; entry count item now accurately reflects enforcement."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҚ® Local Tastes audit вҖ” K2 text check added: 'What it is' / 'Where to find it' visible labels are now caught directly in the Local Tastes entry loop (previously only the CSS class .local-tastes-list was caught via global DRIFT SENTINELS; text labels themselves were not caught). Coverage updated: (1) K2 item clarified to reflect both class and text checks; (2) added 9 new 'yes' items that were enforced in the validator but not documented in Coverage: NAME annotations, рҹ“Қ annotations, NAME not generic, NAME вүӨ50 chars, entry count вүӨ6, extras-empty for negative-finding, structural drift block, section div resolved, spec drift protection."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡ— Food Delivery audit вҖ” 5 fixes: (1) _fd_inner/_fd_is_negative de-duplicated вҖ” _walk_balanced_div was called twice (T9a + T9b); now pre-computed once after _fd_hdr; (2) В§ 2 preference order check added вҖ” DoorDash/Uber Eats (tier 1) вҶ’ Grubhub (tier 2) вҶ’ local (tier 3); entries out of tier order now hard-fail; (3) annotation leakage check updated вҖ” description row removed 2026-05-24 (В§3) but check still indexed into _fdtb_child_divs[1] (which no longer exists); simplified to scan full transit-box body; print label + check label updated from 'description' to 'transit-box'; (4) web search reminder moved from Getting Around block (keyed off getting-around section) to Food Delivery block (keyed off _fd_hdr) вҖ” logically correct placement; (5) stale comment at negative-finding check updated ('set in T9a/T9b blocks above' вҶ’ 'set in pre-computation block above')."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡ• Getting Around dead code removed вҖ” two old-format checks that looked for class='ride-app' elements and a single 'Ride App' extras-sub heading were retired: (1) RIDE-APP NAME ROW SHAPE ENFORCEMENT (checked class='ride-app' + <strong> on name rows вҖ” passed vacuously since 2026-05-24 when per-app format replaced single-block); (2) RIDE APPS вҖ” ENTRY FORMAT CHECK (checked old 3-row name+description+link pattern per class='ride-app' entry вҖ” also vacuous since 2026-05-24); (3) RIDE-APP SUBHEADING EXACT TEXT (checked heading was exactly 'рҹҡ• Ride App' singular вҖ” vacuous since per-app headings use app names like 'рҹҡ• Uber', not 'Ride App'). All three passed vacuously on every current guide."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Rule 401 вҖ” Motion format: вүҘ60 min bare 'N min' is now a hard-FAIL in _validate_motion_row (рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• segments). The Xh Ymin / Xh check already existed (lines ~4886вҖ“4900); the time-stripping step that silently swallowed times after From Hotel: was removed (line 4859 retired вҖ” Rule 402). 41 lines fixed across 9 guides before the validator check landed."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Rule 402 вҖ” From Hotel departure time banned: retired 'TRAIN DAY OPENER вҖ” departure time inline' (which required H:MM am in train-day From Hotel lines) and replaced with hard-FAIL check 'From Hotel вҖ” no departure time' that fires on ANY .hotel-first div containing a time pattern. 12 lines fixed across 8 guides (Paris 3, Munich 4, Sydney, Lisbon, Turin, London, SF 1 each). Motion rule time-strip at line 4859 also removed so times are no longer silently tolerated during pattern validation."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡ© Flag Rows deep-clean вҖ” 8 label/comment fixes: (1) вҸ° format check: added missing 'Pos 4b' citation (Icon Order and Format.html); (2) рҹҡ« format check: added missing 'Pos 3' citation; (3) рҹҶ“ format check: added missing 'Pos 5a' citation; (4) рҹ’ө format check: added missing 'Pos 5b' citation; (5) вҡ пёҸ format check: added missing 'Pos 6' citation; (6вҖ“7) two рҹ“… format checks: removed wrong 'Pos 1' citations (Pos 1 = рҹҺҹ ticket, not рҹ“…) вҖ” replaced with drift-guard note (guided-tour format retired 2026-05-20); (8) B1 comment inside STOP FLAGS вҖ” LOCATION updated from stale 'Guided tour box вҖ” flags forbidden' to explicit drift-guard explanation noting the .tour-box with рҹ“… lead is a retired-format artifact."),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҺҹ ticket-box <strong> check: fixed scoping bug вҖ” if-checks for missing/over-bold <strong> were outside the inner for-tsm loop (only last match per ticket-box was ever evaluated); moved inside the loop so every рҹҺҹ link is checked"),
    ("2026-05-24", 'Tours вҖ” motion row banned suffix: "вҶ’ from hotel" must not appear in a tour entry body; correct format is рҹҡ¶ N min В· рҹҡ• N min only with no directional label (Tours - Extra Section.html В§4)'),
    ("2026-05-24", 'Tours вҖ” "time from hotel" template leakage: hard FAIL if the literal phrase "time from hotel" appears anywhere in the Tours section вҖ” it is a builder instruction in Tours - Extra Section.html В§4 and must be replaced with actual рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• values before shipping'),
    ("2026-05-24", "Banned tour-type synonyms added: cycling tour/tours, bicycle tour/tours, cycle tour/tours (bike tour synonyms); culinary tour/tours, tasting tour/tours, gastro tour/tours (food tour synonyms); e-bike tour/tours, ebike tour/tours (e-bike ban вҖ” Tours - Extra Section.html В§2)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Banned tour-type standalone terms added: 'bike', 'e-bike', 'ebike', 'e bike', 'electric bike', 'bicycle' вҖ” any tour entry containing these words now hard-fails regardless of whether 'tour' follows. Tours section collector updated: now scans <strong> text (tour name only); falls back to <a> text only when <strong> absent."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Wikipedia URL вҡ пёҸ suppression вҖ” bug fix: verify_booking_links.py now writes h1 PASS results into verification_log.json (platform: wikipedia, method: live_fetch, result: PASS) after each live check. Previously h1-match results were printed but never persisted, so the validator's suppression logic could never find a Wikipedia PASS entry and the вҡ пёҸ never cleared. Fix: future_to_item dict replaces zip(futures, h1_required) to correctly map as_completed futures back to their source items; PASS entries written to _build/verification_log.json (creating the file + _meta block if absent)."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Wikipedia URL вҡ пёҸ suppression вҖ” 90-day expiry removed: a PASS entry in verification_log.json (platform: wikipedia, result: PASS) now permanently suppresses the вҡ пёҸ for that URL. Previously a logged PASS expired after 90 days and re-triggered the warning; that re-expiry check (_log_entry_age <= 90) is removed. Warning now fires only for URLs never logged as PASS."),
    ("2026-05-27", '"private" keyword check вҖ” moved from Stops Structure (full-guide text scan, warn) to Tours section block (Tours extras-section only, hard fail). Old check scanned all visible text guide-wide and issued a warning; new check scans only _tours_inner (the Tours extras-section HTML) and calls check() вҖ” hard fail when "private" appears in the Tours section. Validator Coverage updated: warn вҶ’ yes, description updated to reflect Tours-only scope. Guides that had "private" outside the Tours section (e.g. in a map label or prose) no longer trigger.'),
    ("2026-05-26", "Tours extras-sub format enforcement (Tours - Extra Section.html В§6): (1) ts_name_not_strong вҖ” tour name must be first child of <a> wrapped in <strong>; (2) ts_not_encapsulated вҖ” platform В· rating В· reviews must be inside <a>, no text after </a>. Canonical: рҹ“… N. <a><strong>Name</strong> В· Platform В· N.Nвӯҗ В· NNN+ reviews</a>. Both are hard fails."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҠ Metro description вүӨ80 char check now enforced unconditionally вҖ” previously skipped when transit-box shape was wrong (not exactly 3 child divs); now runs on the first child div regardless of total count, so a >80 char description always hard-fails even when the shape check also fires."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Tours city rule вҖ” tour must be held in or depart from the guide city (Tours - Extra Section.html В§1 City rule, added 2026-05-24). Check: tours without рҹҸЁ pickup icon must have рҹ“Қ in guide city; tours with рҹҸЁ pickup from a different city fail. Enforced on extras-sub entries in the Tours section."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Tours motion row: рҹҡ•-only now accepted when meeting point is >40 min walk from hotel (Motion Rule already allows this for banners; Tours check now matches)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Claude Inspiration T1: Skip List footnote (id=skip-list) may follow Inspiration вҖ” it is still last among sections; only non-skip-list extras-sections after CI now fail"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Count minimums now WARN, never hard-fail (per Dani): Cappuccino вүҘ5, Restaurants Near Hotel вүҘ5, Downtown Restaurants вүҘ5, Tours вүҘ5-per-platform, and Tours walking-tours вүҘ2 no longer FAIL when below the target вҖ” genuinely small markets ship what qualifies and document why in the <!-- low-count: [reason] --> comment. A below-minimum section warns; a below-minimum section MISSING its low-count comment also only warns (nudge). Mirrors the Day Trips low-count model. NOTE: only count MINIMUMS were softened вҖ” structural integrity floors (вүҘ1 tour-box, вүҘ1 ticket-box, вүҘ1 overview-day, вүҘ1 рҹҸӣ row per stop-block), per-entry quality bars (Tours 4.5вӯҗ/6-reviews), and the walking-tours MAXIMUM-4 cap remain hard fails."),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹ«• Restaurants Near Hotel suffix check: cuisine or any plain text after the review link in extras-sub now fails вҖ” heading format is [Restaurant] В· [review link] only; cuisine belongs on line 2 of entry-body (Restaurants Near Hotel - Extra Section.html В§ 5b)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҚҪпёҸ Downtown Restaurants suffix check: cuisine or any plain text after the review link in extras-sub now fails вҖ” heading format is [Restaurant] В· [review link] only; cuisine belongs on line 2 of entry-body (Downtown Restaurants - Extra Section.html В§ 6)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "вҳ• Cappuccino suffix check (T4d): any plain text after the review link in extras-sub now fails вҖ” heading format is [CafГ©] В· [review link] only (Cappuccino - Extra Section.html В§ 3)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Section title enforcement tightened: 'Restaurants Near Hotel' вҖ” bare 'Restaurants' alias removed, only 'рҹ«• Restaurants Near Hotel' accepted; 'Downtown Restaurants' вҖ” bare 'Downtown' alias removed, only 'рҹҚҪпёҸ Downtown Restaurants' accepted. Wrong titles now hard-fail."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Section title enforcement вҖ” all sections: canonical title added as comment under each required_extras entry; 'рҹҺӯ Shows' alias removed вҖ” only 'рҹҺӯ Shows, Performances & Concerts' accepted; all other section titles verified exact against their rules files. Hard-fail on any deviation."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Section renames applied everywhere: 'Stations Near the Hotel' вҶ’ 'Train Stations Near Hotel', 'Near the Hotel' вҶ’ 'Restaurants Near Hotel'; required_extras regex patterns updated to match new canonical titles"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҺҹ Free hard fail: any рҹҺҹ div containing 'free', 'no booking', or 'no reservation' now fails вҖ” only рҹҶ“ may mark a free/no-booking venue; 'рҹҺҹ Free вҖ” no booking needed' is always wrong (locked 2026-05-24 вҖ” Marrakech Jemaa el-Fnaa drift)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” bus station entries: any extras-sub whose name contains 'bus' must follow train-station format (station-box wrapper + рҹ“Қ address + motion row); hard fail on any missing element (locked 2026-05-24)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” рҹҺҹ booking link aggregator guard: any рҹҺҹ row in #stations-near-hotel must link to the rail/bus operator, not Viator / Get Your Guide / TripAdvisor / any 'tours' site вҖ” hard fail (locked 2026-05-24)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Food review link domain check: class='review-link' href in Cappuccino / Restaurants Near Hotel / Downtown Restaurants must point to Yelp, Google Reviews, or Local Guide вҖ” not venue's own site, not Viator, not TripAdvisor (Cappuccino В§ 3 / RNH В§ 4b / Downtown В§ 5, locked 2026-05-24)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Train Day вҖ” рҹҺ« booking row now required on BOTH outbound and return train-headers: every рҹҡҠ/рҹҡ„ train-header must carry a рҹҺ« book at: [Train Ticket Operator] row between the header and div.train; old check that required the return to NOT have рҹҺ« is retired; Stops Structure.html В§5 return block updated to include рҹҺ« row"),
    ("2026-05-24", "рҹҡ— Food Delivery false positive fixed: embedded \\x08 backspace byte in regex <a[^>]*> corrupted it to <a\\x08[^>]*> (then to <a[[^>]*> after partial repair) вҖ” <a> stripping never matched so link text was left behind as 'description text'; fixed to correct <a[^>]*>.*?</a>"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Trip Overview icon-sync: .guided modifier retired 2026-05-20 вҖ” stale mixed/guided branches removed; any .stop-name.guided class now hard-fails regardless of mixed or pure day (Stops Structure.html В§2 вҖ” only рҹҺ’ Self-Guided and рҹҡҶ Train Day are active)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Trip Overview extras pills canonical order check added: .overview-extra-link pill hrefs must appear in the same relative sequence as eoi_canonical_order (Guide Structure.html / Trip Overview.html В§3); out-of-order pills now hard-fail"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Tours В§1 city rule вҖ” not automatable: В§6 address format omits the guide city from local addresses (street + neighborhood only), so absence of the city name in рҹ“Қ text is always correct, not a violation; rule must be enforced at build time (вқҢ human in Validator Coverage)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Tours В§1 walking tour cap added: guide must have minimum 2 and maximum 4 walking tours across all platforms combined (counted by 'walking' in extras-sub name); hard-fail outside the 2вҖ“4 range"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Downtown Restaurants dead postal-code code removed: _DR_POSTAL_RE compile + dr_no_postal_code population were dead since 2026-05-19 rule reversal; declaration and entry-loop code cleaned up"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Downtown Restaurants inverse negative-finding check added (E-inv): when entries are present, 'No restaurants in downtown [City].' must NOT appear вҖ” same pattern as Cappuccino / Day Trips / Pickleball inverse checks"),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹ«• Restaurants Near Hotel stale-label cleanup: section header/print renamed NEAR THE HOTEL вҶ’ RESTAURANTS NEAR HOTEL; all В§4a вҶ’ В§5a and В§4b вҶ’ В§5b references corrected throughout RNH code block; 'shows-box row order' вҶ’ 'entry row order' in row-order check label; 'Top 4' вҶ’ 'Minimum 5' in walk-distance check label (per 2026-05-23 rule change that raised minimum to 5)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹ«• Restaurants Near Hotel tram exemption: missing-рҹҡ• FAIL now skipped when рҹҡҺ tram is present in entry body (В§5b tram alternative: рҹҡ¶ X min вҶ’ рҹҡҺ [N] вҶ’ рҹҡ¶ T min; validator previously always failed on missing рҹҡ• even when a valid tram route was provided)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹ«• Restaurants Near Hotel вҖ” five new checks added: (A) annotation leakage ([UPDATE]/рҹ”ҙ/[TBD] etc. in heading or entry body hard-fail); (B) no <p> tags inside entry body (section uses row divs, not paragraphs); (C) duplicate restaurant names within section (copy-paste error); (D) inverse negative-finding (entries present вҶ’ 'No restaurants within 25 min walk' must NOT appear); (E) no preamble prose before first entry (В§5 starts immediately with entries, no intro paragraph). All five match the Cappuccino/Downtown pattern."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Shows dead postal-code code removed: _SHOWS_POSTAL_RE compile + shows_no_postal_code population were dead since 2026-05-19 rule reversal (global postal-code check covers all sections per user: 'shows_no_postal_code we dont need by section this should be global fail')"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Shows OвҖ“W checks implemented: 9 phantom variables (O=<p> tags in shows-box, P=no intro preamble, Q=descвүҘ10chars, R=desc plain text no links, S=ticket link text non-empty, T=no star in heading, U=motion dot separator, V=walk time integer, W=inverse negative-finding) were declared but never populated or checked вҖ” all now enforced"),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҢ Getting Around dead-code removal: (1) orphan stale comment '# RIDE APPS EMPTY-CASE NEGATIVE FINDING' removed; (2) old single-block empty-case check (regex matching legacy 'рҹҡ• Ride apps' heading) retired вҖ” superseded 2026-05-19 by per-app extras-sub entries; (3) old ride-app link-row check (class=ride-app divs) retired вҖ” class no longer exists in current guides; active coverage is the PER-APP TRANSIT-BOX LINK-ONLY block (added 2026-05-24). Garbled check label fixed: 'вҖ” = ride apps' corrected to 'В§1 вҖ” ride apps must be first'."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҸӣ Stop Titles вҖ” .guided modifier hard-fail completed: MOD_CLASSES changed from ('guided', 'self') to ('self',) вҖ” any .stop-name.guided now fails check (A) as 'missing modifier' (guided retired 2026-05-20, per Stops Structure.html В§2); guided branch in check (C) retired as dead code; check (D) comment updated (Type 3 Alternation retired along with guided); check (A) and (C) labels updated to reflect self-only; mutual-exclusion tombstone comment updated; Coverage item 100 'to-do' note resolved."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Michelin dead postal-code code removed: _mich_postal_re compile + mich_no_postal_code population were dead since 2026-05-19 rule reversal; declaration and entry-loop code cleaned up (same pattern as Downtown Restaurants K / Shows H removals)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҸ“ Pickleball audit вҖ” 4 fixes: (1) stale aliases pb_body/pb_body_sfx/_pb_body_shape removed вҖ” all references now use _pb_inner directly (no logic change, eliminates confusion); (2) retired redundant global description-length check for Pickleball вҖ” per-entry shape check already handles вүӨ80 chars with accurate icon positions; global check used a 'first non-empty div' heuristic that could misfire on empty-description entries; (3) removed ~? from walk time regex (r'рҹҡ¶\\s*(\\d+)\\s*min') вҖ” tilde must no longer silently pass; added dedicated no-tilde scan over each entry's text body (same pattern as WC-X6, hardcoded per Motion Rule); (4) В§ 3 address format: added per-entry checks for postal code (US ZIP 5-digit) and country names in the рҹ“Қ row вҖ” both are explicitly banned by Pickleball - Extra Section.html В§3; _PB_COUNTRY_RE pre-compiled before entry loop."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹ“’ Stop Descriptions audit (Icon Order and Format.html В§ 2 Pos 1) вҖ” 2 fixes: (1) dead check removed: _shows_gap_hits was always [] (rule retired 2026-05-15 вҖ” no рҹ“’ required before shows-box); declaration + check() call both removed, comment retained as tombstone; (2) annotation leakage check added: [UPDATE]/[CHECK]/рҹ”ҙ/[TBD] etc. in рҹ“’ description text now hard-fail вҖ” scoped to stop-block bodies (reuses _stop_block_bodies_desc); same pattern as stop-name annotation leakage, WC-ANNOT, and CAP-ANNOT. Coverage confirmed complete: length вүӨ320, no links, required on every stop-block, no merged рҹ“’рҹ“–, no рҹ“’ inside tour-box, рҹ“– order (before/immediately-after) all previously enforced."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” entry format updated: station heading (extras-sub) must now start with рҹҡҶ (local/regional) or рҹҡ„ (high-speed); hard-fail when icon prefix is absent. Route-row ban exempted for extras-sub (was incorrectly catching the icon prefix). CORE RULES В§ 3 split into В§ 3a Local & Regional Stations (рҹҡҶ [Station Name]) and В§ 3b High-Speed Stations (рҹҡ„ [Station Name]). Checksum updated."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” stop-block checks: (1) every .stop-block must contain at least one рҹҸӣпёҸ opening-hours row (hard fail); (2) no .stop-block may have a рҹҡ¶ walk time > 40 min (hard fail). Both scoped to main itinerary stop-blocks only, not extra sections."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” reverted inline-icon-in-body check: the 2026-05-25 check requiring both рҹҡҶ and рҹҡ„ in the entry body was wrong. Per В§ 3a/В§3b, the icon belongs on the heading (extras-sub) only; description row is plain [Lines] вҶ’ [Key Destinations]. Check removed; heading-icon enforcement (already present) is sufficient."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҰ Motion Rule В§1 time-format enforcement вҖ” рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• times вүҘ60 min must use Xh Ymin (or Xh when Y=0); 'N min' with NвүҘ60 now hard-fails with a suggested correction. _unit_re updated to strip Xh Ymin in leftover-prose check. Motion Rule.html В§1 updated with explicit format rule."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҰ Motion / Transit Banners audit (Motion Rule.html) вҖ” 1 fix: dead guided-stop рҹҡҗ block removed (lines 4842вҖ“4910, ~70 lines). The .guided CSS class was retired 2026-05-20; _guided_sn_re always returned False on all current guides; _guided_next_violations was always []; check() passed vacuously every run. Tombstone comment added. Coverage verified complete against all three rule sections: В§1 stops pattern (рҹҡ¶/рҹҡ• N min, tram/metro inline) вҖ” _validate_motion_row; В§2 extra sections with motion (Cappuccino, RNH, Stations, Pickleball, Shows) and without (Downtown, Local Tastes, Michelin, Heads Up) вҖ” each has dedicated row-type enforcement; В§3 day wrapper (opener, between-stops, closer, train variants, рҹҡү ARRIVE banner) вҖ” covered by opener/closer/bookend/train-header/arrive-first checks. No gaps found."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Trip Overview extras pill label text hard-fail added: every .overview-extra-link visible label must exactly match the canonical name defined in Trip Overview.html В§ 3 (owner-defined decisions, not formatting). _OVERVIEW_PILL_CANONICAL_LABELS dict maps href anchor вҶ’ required label text. Canonical labels: weekly-closuresвҶ’'рҹ—“пёҸ Weekly Closures', toursвҶ’'рҹ“… Tours', cappuccinoвҶ’'вҳ• Cappuccino', restaurantsвҶ’'рҹ«• Restaurants Near Hotel', downtownвҶ’'рҹҚҪпёҸ Downtown Restaurants', local-tastesвҶ’'рҹҚ® Local Tastes', food-deliveryвҶ’'рҹҡ— Food Delivery', showsвҶ’'рҹҺӯ Shows', getting-aroundвҶ’'рҹҡҢ Getting Around', stations-near-hotelвҶ’'рҹҡҶ Stations Near Hotel', day-tripsвҶ’'вӣІпёҸ Day Trips by Train', pickleballвҶ’'рҹҸ“ Pickleball', michelinвҶ’'вӯҗ Michelin Restaurants', heads-upвҶ’'вқ— Heads Up'. All 16 guides updated to match."),
    ("2026-05-25", "рҹҡҰ Motion Rule вҖ” two consecutive motion rows hard-fail: any two adjacent <div> rows both starting with рҹҡ¶ or рҹҡ• inside the same box (shows-box, entry-body, station-box) are a hard fail. рҹҡ¶ and рҹҡ• must share a single row ('рҹҡ¶ N min В· рҹҡ• M min'); splitting them is format drift. Scoped to extras boxes only (stop-blocks enforce via _validate_motion_row already)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Food review link format check вҖ” outer regex blind-spot fixed: _food_review_re previously matched only class='review-link' anchors whose text already contained вӯҗ AND 'reviews'; anchors with wrong text (вҳ… star, no star, no 'reviews') were silently invisible and passed. Outer regex changed from ([^<]*вӯҗ[^<]*reviews[^<]*) to ([^<]+) вҖ” ALL class='review-link' anchors are now validated against the N.Nвӯҗ В· N+ reviews format. Applies to Cappuccino / Restaurants Near Hotel / Downtown (all 3 food sections)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Food review link вҖ” must have class='review-link' check added: any <a> in .extras-sub whose text matches the rating pattern (N.Nвӯҗ В· N+ reviews) must carry class='review-link'. Without it, CSS rule '.extras-sub a { color: inherit; font-weight: inherit }' renders the link dark+bold (heading color) instead of blue (#2867c4) + normal weight. New hard-fail covers all 3 food sections (Cappuccino / RNH / Downtown)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Food review link вҖ” no <strong> inside review-link check added: a <strong> tag inside class='review-link' overrides the CSS font-weight:normal rule, making the rating text bold. New hard-fail catches any <strong> inside any class='review-link' anchor."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҺҹ ticket-box star rating regex tightened: _star_rating_re changed from \\d+\\.?\\d*\\s*вӯҗ (decimal optional, space before star allowed) to \\d+\\.\\dвӯҗ (decimal required, no space). Old pattern accepted '4вӯҗ' (integer, no decimal) and '4.5 вӯҗ' (space before star) вҖ” both violate the tight N.Nвӯҗ format rule (locked 2026-05-20). Ticket entries must use exactly N.Nвӯҗ with one decimal place."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” transport icons banned from description row: рҹҡҶ and рҹҡ„ must appear only on the extras-sub heading, never inside the station-box description row. Per В§ 3a/В§3b, description row is plain [Lines] вҶ’ [Key Destinations] вҖ” no transport icons. New hard-fail scans the first content row of each station entry and fails when рҹҡҶ or рҹҡ„ is found there (e.g. 'Alfa Pendular рҹҡ„ connection hub' is a fail)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҡ· Skip List cross-check вҖ” venues named in the skip list must not also appear as tour entries in the Tours section. Skip = intentionally excluded; shipping the same venue as a tour contradicts the editorial decision. Hard-fail: extracts significant keywords (вүҘ5 chars, not generic travel words) from each skip-list item and checks if any keyword appears in a Tours extras-sub heading."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹ’Ў Claude Inspiration T1b вҖ” Skip List before CI hard-fail added: when both claude-inspiration and skip-list are present, skip-list must appear AFTER claude-inspiration (correct order: claude-inspiration вҶ’ skip-list). Prior T1 check only enforced that non-skip-list sections don't follow CI; it never checked skip-list appearing before CI вҖ” silent gap fixed."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҡҶ Train Stations Near Hotel вҖ” non-rail transport words banned from description row: bus В· car В· plane В· airplane В· aircraft В· flight В· ferry В· coach В· taxi В· shuttle must not appear in the station-box description row. Section is rail-only; any of these words in a description row indicates drift into other transport modes. Hard-fail on whole-word match (case-insensitive)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҡў Ferry added as motion icon (position 8e): inline transit row format 'рҹҡў N min вҶ’ [Destination]' and Getting Around section entry (вүӨ80 chars). Validator updated: рҹҡў added to _first_motion ARRIVE-banner search, row trigger for _validate_motion_row, and _MOTION_LEAD_RE consecutive-motion check. Rules updated: Motion Rule.html В§1, Icon Order and Format.html В§2 row 8e + В§3 Getting Around, Emoji Library moved from available to reserved."),
    ("2026-05-26", "вӣІпёҸ Day Trips renamed to Day Trips by Train everywhere: CORE RULES file, section title, anchor id (day-trips-by-train), validator canonical references, all 16 guides, Coverage, Dependency Map. day-trips is now the legacy backward-compat id. Non-train transport language check expanded from headings-only to full section content (drive/car/taxi/bus/ride/shuttle/etc.)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "DECISION LOCKS block added to validator: positive assertions that major decisions cannot drift back. Locks: (1) walk cap >44 min hard fail with no sentinel override; (2) Day Trips by Train вҖ” title must say 'by Train', anchor must be day-trips-by-train, build_state.md must reference renamed file; (3) рҹҺ« format must always be 'рҹҺ« book at: <link>' globally вҖ” no bare рҹҺ« without prefix. Complements existing retired-pattern drift sentinels (which ban old patterns) with required-pattern locks (which assert current standards). CORE RULES files fixed: Trip Overview anchor updated to #day-trips-by-train; Icon Order and Format рҹҺ« sub-row label updated to 'Day Trips by Train booking'. Build_state.md in all 16 guides updated from Day Trips - Extra Section.html вҶ’ Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html. Pasadena negative finding rewritten (removed 'car' вҖ” banned word). Sydney orphaned transit divs removed."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҡҠ LEAVE banner вҖ” .leave-first class introduced (2026-05-26): replaces the .next div that was shadowing рҹҡҶ for station-bound return motion; 7 guides updated (Lisbon, Turin, London, ParisГ—3, Sydney); guide_v2.css updated (.leave-first = same blue banner as .arrive-first). Validator: leave-first added to all banner regex patterns and class lists; TRAIN-DAY LEAVE warn check (missing .leave-first per train-day block); рҹҡҠ LEAVE format check (hard-fail if .leave-first does not start with 'рҹҡҠ LEAVE {city}:'); drift sentinel (hard-fail if .next div heads to a train station вҖ” must be .leave-first)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "рҹҡҠвҶ’рҹҡқ metro icon reassignment + рҹҡҠ LEAVE banner added: metro icon changed from рҹҡҠ to рҹҡқ in Getting Around В§3, Motion Rule В§1, Icon Order В§2 row 8d; рҹҡҠ LEAVE {station} banner added to Motion Rule В§3b and Icon Order В§4 row 5 as departure counterpart to рҹҡү ARRIVE. Validator: рҹҡҠвҶ’рҹҡқ in _GA_ALLOWED_ICONS, _GA_ICONS_RE, metro section detection, all Metro A/B/C check labels; рҹҡқ added to _logistic_lead and arrive-strip motion search. Drift sentinel: old рҹҡҠ-as-metro section heading hard-fails. CORE RULES updated: Getting Around - Extra Section.html В§3, Motion Rule.html В§1 + В§3b, Icon Order and Format.html В§2 8d + В§4 rows 4вҖ“5."),
    ("2026-05-26", "вӣІпёҸ Day Trips by Train вҖ” Omio check added: every рҹҺ« booking row in a Day Trips transit-box must include an omio.com link (hard fail). Per Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html В§2 entry format: 'рҹҺ« book at: [Train Ticket Operator] or [Omio]'. Coverage: Day Trips 15 вҶ’ 16 items."),
